1115
01:09:50,915 --> 01:09:53,349
You're already heroes. Just
sit back and enjoy the ride.

1116
01:09:53,418 --> 01:09:55,545
[Man Chattering On Radio]

1117
01:09:55,620 --> 01:09:58,020
We're T minus 20 seconds.

1118
01:09:58,089 --> 01:10:00,216
[Chattering Continues]

1119
01:10:00,291 --> 01:10:04,523
Ten. Nine. Eight. Seven.

1120
01:10:04,596 --> 01:10:08,623
Four. Three. Two. One.

1121
01:10:08,700 --> 01:10:12,761
- [Roaring]
- We have main engine start.

1122
01:10:12,837 --> 01:10:15,362
- We have booster ignition.
- We're going.

1123
01:10:15,440 --> 01:10:18,102
And liftoff.

1124
01:10:27,752 --> 01:10:31,119
- Freedom, this is flight deck.
- [Sharp On Radio]

1125
01:10:31,189 --> 01:10:33,054
Roger, Freedom. You're looking good.

1126
01:10:46,070 --> 01:10:50,939
- We have go for Independence.
- Three. Two. One.

1127
01:10:51,009 --> 01:10:54,069
- Independence, we have booster ignition.
- [Chattering Continues]

1128
01:10:54,145 --> 01:10:57,876
- We have liftoff.
- We are cooking, Houston.

1129
01:11:19,437 --> 01:11:21,871
Houston, the tower is clear.
They're all yours.

1130
01:11:21,940 --> 01:11:23,965
[Cheering]

1131
01:11:24,042 --> 01:11:27,170
- [Shuttles Roaring]
- Heads up, everybody. They're ours now.

1132
01:11:27,245 --> 01:11:30,544
- All engines are go.
- Keep a sharp eye out on both of 'em.

1133
01:11:30,615 --> 01:11:33,914
[Radio Chatter Continues]

1134
01:11:37,689 --> 01:11:40,214
[Sharp]
Start roll maneuver.

1135
01:11:50,268 --> 01:11:53,567
- Two good roll programs. - One
down. - Independence, we have max cue.

1136
01:11:53,638 --> 01:11:55,572
Roger, Control. We are a max cue.

1137
01:11:57,675 --> 01:12:00,109
- S.R.B. Sep...
- [Engines Roaring]

1138
01:12:04,282 --> 01:12:07,581
- We are single-engine, press, demi-go.
- Copy, press, demi-go.

1139
01:12:07,652 --> 01:12:09,813
Houston, this is a kick-ass ride!

1140
01:12:15,626 --> 01:12:18,754
Freedom, this is Houston.
Main engine cut out on schedule. Out.

1141
01:12:18,830 --> 01:12:21,560
[Engines Cut Out]

1142
01:12:28,940 --> 01:12:31,170
Freedom, stats are good.

1143
01:12:35,613 --> 01:12:38,605
- Independence, telemetry is up and running.
- Oh, my God.

1144
01:12:38,683 --> 01:12:42,517
This is space! 'Course, we're just
in the beginning part of space.

1145
01:12:42,587 --> 01:12:45,112
We-We haven't gotten to outer space yet.

1146
01:12:45,189 --> 01:12:48,522
Roger, Houston. We have a visual on the
Russian space station. Initiating retro burn.

1147
01:12:51,129 --> 01:12:54,826
Gentlemen, remember the Russian space
station has been up there for 11 years.

1148
01:12:54,899 --> 01:12:57,265
Most of us don't have cars that old.

1149
01:12:57,335 --> 01:13:01,203
Now, the cosmonaut on board has been
on that tin can for 18 months, alone.

1150
01:13:03,674 --> 01:13:06,609
So don't be surprised
if he's a little... off.

1151
01:13:06,677 --> 01:13:09,441
- Independence, we're gonna put you...
- All right, crew.

1152
01:13:09,514 --> 01:13:11,383
- Let's exit these flight suits.
- [Laughing]

1153
01:13:11,516 --> 01:13:13,484
[Russian Accent] Hello.

1154
01:13:13,551 --> 01:13:17,419
This is Russian space station.
Can you hear me?

1155
01:13:17,489 --> 01:13:20,617
[Speaks Russian] We copy, Russian
space station. This is Houston.

1156
01:13:20,692 --> 01:13:24,253
I'm ready to fire my thrusters any time.

1157
01:13:24,329 --> 01:13:27,787
- Stand by.
- Okay. I'm not going anywhere.

1158
01:13:27,866 --> 01:13:30,801
We have a go.
Initiate gravitational spin.

1159
01:13:30,869 --> 01:13:35,829
- [Chattering On Radio]
- [Thrusters Roaring]

1160
01:13:37,842 --> 01:13:41,073
- You are maxed at 40-percent spin.
- [Moans]

1161
01:13:42,347 --> 01:13:45,077
Okay, Houston.

1162
01:13:45,150 --> 01:13:49,917
I can feel I'm having gravity.

1163
01:13:49,988 --> 01:13:52,855
All right, gentlemen.
We're gonna dock in a minute.

1164
01:13:52,924 --> 01:13:54,858
Now, the Russian space station
has fired her rockets...

1165
01:13:54,926 --> 01:13:57,292
- Whee!
- To simulate gravity and let us work faster.

1166
01:13:57,362 --> 01:13:59,523
It's gonna make you queasy,
so prepare yourself.

1167
01:13:59,597 --> 01:14:04,034
- Well, it's about time. I haven't thrown up in about an hour.
- [Laughing]

1168
01:14:07,138 --> 01:14:10,403
Initiating first phase
of docking procedure.

1169
01:14:10,475 --> 01:14:13,603
- Switching to manual.
- Manual override.

1170
01:14:19,250 --> 01:14:23,880
One foot per second. Let's take this
slow and do it right, folks. Twenty feet.

1171
01:14:25,657 --> 01:14:28,285
- [Blipping]
- Ten feet.

1172
01:14:28,359 --> 01:14:32,693
Looking good on radar. Five feet.

1173
01:14:32,764 --> 01:14:36,700
[Clanking, Hissing]

1174
01:14:36,768 --> 01:14:40,397
Locks are engaged. Fuel teams, let's go.

1175
01:14:40,472 --> 01:14:43,464
Freedom, telemetry is looking good.

1176
01:14:43,541 --> 01:14:45,839
- [Hissing]
- We have soft dock.

1177
01:14:45,910 --> 01:14:49,402
[Sharp]
Fuel teams, prepare to unload.

1178
01:14:53,084 --> 01:14:55,018
All right, gentlemen, watch your heads.

1179
01:14:55,086 --> 01:14:57,020
Let's go, Independence.

1180
01:14:59,557 --> 01:15:02,492
Colonel.

1181
01:15:02,560 --> 01:15:05,495
¤ [Russian Folk]

1182
01:15:11,569 --> 01:15:15,767
Where is he? Anybody home?

1183
01:15:15,840 --> 01:15:18,570
Welcome, everybody!

1184
01:15:20,645 --> 01:15:25,309
I am not gas station. This is
sophisticated laboratory. I'm in charge.

1185
01:15:25,383 --> 01:15:28,511
So do not be touching anything.

1186
01:15:28,586 --> 01:15:31,851
- I need one... I need you.
- Go with him.

1187
01:15:31,923 --> 01:15:33,788
I need you. Hurry up.
Hurry up. Come on. Come on.

1188
01:15:33,858 --> 01:15:38,761
It's very important you watch
the fuel gauge, okay? Put on cold suit.

1189
01:15:38,830 --> 01:15:41,628
- Countdown clock will hold at...
- Copy that, Houston. Prepping for fuel transfer.

1190
01:15:41,699 --> 01:15:44,133
Countdown clock will hold
at T minus 20 minutes and...

1191
01:15:44,202 --> 01:15:46,466
Fuel pod is down there.

1192
01:15:46,538 --> 01:15:48,768
It's down here, huh? Great.

1193
01:15:48,840 --> 01:15:50,899
[Hissing]

1194
01:15:50,975 --> 01:15:53,944
[All Chattering]

1195
01:15:58,850 --> 01:16:01,284
Okay, let's connect these fuel lines.

1196
01:16:04,022 --> 01:16:06,490
Freedom on the left,
Independence on the right.

1197
01:16:06,558 --> 01:16:08,492
All right. We're goin' left here.

1198
01:16:10,962 --> 01:16:15,831
To the right is fuel gauge. You watch
the fuel gauge. One fifty, okay.

1199
01:16:15,900 --> 01:16:20,997
One sixty, okay. Two hundred,
bad disaster for space station.

1200
01:16:21,072 --> 01:16:26,635
So if you watch 200, you call for Lev,
on, and you see here number one. Off.

1201
01:16:26,711 --> 01:16:29,475
You ask for Lev. And you pull
this down, all the way down.

1202
01:16:29,547 --> 01:16:34,507
- What's Lev?
- I am Lev Andropov, colonel of Russian space agency.

1203
01:16:34,586 --> 01:16:37,851
In Russia I'm a very big man.

1204
01:16:37,922 --> 01:16:41,153
- We're ready to transfer.
- I'm coming. No problem.

1205
01:16:41,225 --> 01:16:43,659
[All Chattering]

1206
01:16:43,728 --> 01:16:46,288
You. You. You there!

1207
01:16:46,364 --> 01:16:50,266
- Hard locked.
- Ready for transfusion!

1208
01:16:50,335 --> 01:16:53,270
- [Beeps]
- [Hissing]

1209
01:16:58,209 --> 01:17:00,871
[Lev] Fuel is pumping.

1210
01:17:00,945 --> 01:17:03,812
How long have you been up here
on your own, man?

1211
01:17:03,881 --> 01:17:07,715
- Uh, eighteen months now.
- That's a long-ass time.

1212
01:17:07,785 --> 01:17:12,245
Lev, I am so sorry about all the
upheaval and strife in your country.

1213
01:17:12,323 --> 01:17:15,019
Man, that must be tough
up here with the loneliness.

1214
01:17:15,093 --> 01:17:17,186
But I want you to know
that up here...

1215
01:17:17,295 --> 01:17:20,526
there are no Russians and there are
no Americans, we're just spacemen.

1216
01:17:20,598 --> 01:17:24,034
[Men Shouting]
We got it, we got it, we got it!

1217
01:17:28,072 --> 01:17:31,303
I'm gonna check down here
with these guys.

1218
01:17:34,946 --> 01:17:37,540
Hey, Lev, the, uh,
the-the pressure's climbing.

1219
01:17:37,615 --> 01:17:39,549
[A.J. Continues, Radio Static Hissing]

1220
01:17:39,617 --> 01:17:41,642
Still, we're on fuel transference.

1221
01:17:41,719 --> 01:17:43,983
Don't touch my uncle. You know?

1222
01:17:44,055 --> 01:17:45,989
He's a genius of my family.

1223
01:17:46,057 --> 01:17:50,960
- [Hissing]
- Lev! Can anybody hear me? Guys? Hello, guys!

1224
01:17:51,029 --> 01:17:53,657
- [No Audio]
- He used to work for a big bomb factory.

1225
01:17:53,731 --> 01:17:56,529
He used to make the tip
of the bomb, the thing...

1226
01:17:56,601 --> 01:17:59,570
that finds, uh, New York
or Washington, you know?

1227
01:17:59,637 --> 01:18:03,596
- Ooh.
- Check your hoses. We got some thermal variation.

1228
01:18:03,675 --> 01:18:06,235
Stamper, let's look at the couplings,
back on the shuttle.

1229
01:18:09,213 --> 01:18:12,148
Okay. Shut down. Uh...

1230
01:18:12,216 --> 01:18:15,310
[Grunting]

1231
01:18:15,386 --> 01:18:17,354
[Motors Grinding Down]

1232
01:18:17,422 --> 01:18:19,686
Uh... Guys!

1233
01:18:19,757 --> 01:18:22,089
[Sharp] What's that noise?

1234
01:18:23,695 --> 01:18:26,858
Oh, no! God!

1235
01:18:28,966 --> 01:18:31,127
What is it?

1236
01:18:31,202 --> 01:18:33,397
[Shouting In Russian]
Leak! Leak!

1237
01:18:35,339 --> 01:18:38,536
Get your men back to the shuttle! Go!

1238
01:18:39,610 --> 01:18:42,875
Go! Hurry up! Get out of there!

1239
01:18:42,947 --> 01:18:46,348
- You know, this really smarts!
- Pull lever!

1240
01:18:46,417 --> 01:18:49,215
This is the lever!

1241
01:18:49,287 --> 01:18:53,087
- Colonel, we must get him out of there!
- A.J., come on out!

1242
01:18:54,726 --> 01:18:58,127
- Aah! Aah!
- Hurry! Hurry!

1243
01:19:01,099 --> 01:19:03,158
Emergency break away!

1244
01:19:03,234 --> 01:19:06,169
We got a fire in the fuel pod!

1245
01:19:08,940 --> 01:19:12,933
- Come on!
- Come on! Get in here! A.J.'s stuck in the fuel pod!

1246
01:19:15,079 --> 01:19:17,343
- We're losing it!
- [All Shouting]

1247
01:19:23,087 --> 01:19:25,419
[All Shouting]

1248
01:19:28,526 --> 01:19:30,619
Control, this is Independence.
I am seeing vibration...

1249
01:19:32,597 --> 01:19:34,292
[All Shouting]

1250
01:19:34,365 --> 01:19:36,856
- Malloy, talk to me!
- Not good. We got sparks and fire in the fuel pod.

1251
01:19:36,934 --> 01:19:39,300
Independence, blow those locks
and get outta there now!

1252
01:19:39,370 --> 01:19:41,304
Dump the hoses now! We're going!

1253
01:19:41,372 --> 01:19:45,308
- What happened? Let me shut off the O2 feed!
- Harry, it's burnin' up!

1254
01:19:45,376 --> 01:19:47,867
Damn! Max, Rock, get in here!

1255
01:19:47,945 --> 01:19:50,140
Get down there and crack
these pipes over here!

1256
01:19:50,214 --> 01:19:54,019
- Harry, it's burnin' up!
- We're goin' back for the other team!

1257
01:19:54,152 --> 01:19:57,178
- [Chatter On Radio]
- [Man] Switch on the personnel locators.

1258
01:19:57,255 --> 01:19:59,621
Trackin' A.J. He's climbin'.

1259
01:19:59,691 --> 01:20:02,159
- No!
- Go! Go!

1260
01:20:02,227 --> 01:20:05,993
It's too late! Get back to the shuttle!
This thing's gonna blow!

1261
01:20:06,064 --> 01:20:08,430
No!

1262
01:20:08,500 --> 01:20:12,994
Colonel, we gotta move now!
Come on! Close the hatch!

1263
01:20:13,071 --> 01:20:15,539
Wait a minute! Wait a minute!
We got a man in there!

1264
01:20:15,607 --> 01:20:18,405
- Open that door, and we'll all die!
- Fuel leak!

1265
01:20:18,476 --> 01:20:21,309
[All Shouting]

1266
01:20:21,379 --> 01:20:24,007
Evac now! Let's go! Let's go!

1267
01:20:26,017 --> 01:20:29,680
Come on back! No, wait!
The door is broken!

1268
01:20:31,056 --> 01:20:33,490
- No!
- They got the fire sealed in the fuel pod.

1269
01:20:33,558 --> 01:20:35,753
- They locked it down.
- [Man On P.A.] Tracking men to the shuttle.

1270
01:20:35,827 --> 01:20:37,886
They've still got
two men trapped in there!

1271
01:20:39,664 --> 01:20:44,101
Keep running! The shuttle's another
75 feet! Where's the rest of the team?

1272
01:20:44,169 --> 01:20:46,467
- [All Shouting]
- Where's A.J.?

1273
01:20:46,538 --> 01:20:49,098
- A.J.'s gone!
- We're not leavin' without A.J.!

1274
01:20:49,174 --> 01:20:52,075
He's gone! It's too late!

1275
01:20:52,143 --> 01:20:55,544
Come on! This way is our only chance!

1276
01:20:55,613 --> 01:20:58,138
So it's minus hundred!

1277
01:20:58,216 --> 01:21:01,379
Very cold. Hold breath, or lung freezes!

1278
01:21:06,958 --> 01:21:10,223
- [Shouting]
- Get back to the shuttle! And lock that door!

1279
01:21:10,295 --> 01:21:15,198
[All Shouting]

1280
01:21:15,266 --> 01:21:19,726
- It's on fire! It's on fire, Harry!
- It's them or all of us!

1281
01:21:19,804 --> 01:21:22,705
- It's on fire. - Full
thrust. - We're gonna get hit.

1282
01:21:26,544 --> 01:21:29,809
[Rattling, Hissing]

1283
01:21:36,154 --> 01:21:38,315
[Gasping]

1284
01:21:39,390 --> 01:21:44,327
Lev! Lev, the door's gonna blow!

1285
01:21:44,395 --> 01:21:46,420
No!

1286
01:21:48,166 --> 01:21:52,865
- Oh!
- We're going! It's gonna blow!

1287
01:21:52,937 --> 01:21:58,307
- A.J.'s still in there! - Blow the
locks. No, the bolts! - We've gotta...

1288
01:21:58,376 --> 01:22:02,813
- I think we're almost there!
- [All Shouting]

1289
01:22:02,881 --> 01:22:05,577
Flight, Independence does not have A.J.
They're gonna close the door without him.

1290
01:22:05,650 --> 01:22:07,584
[Man] Tracking.
They're 75 feet from the shuttle.

1291
01:22:07,652 --> 01:22:10,519
- Just tell 'em to air lock the door and go!
- Dog the hatch now!

1292
01:22:10,588 --> 01:22:12,647
- Close it!
- [Explosion]

1293
01:22:16,661 --> 01:22:19,129
- Ho...
- [Exploding]

1294
01:22:19,197 --> 01:22:23,896
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Colonel! That thing's
comin' right for... We got to move!

1295
01:22:27,172 --> 01:22:31,905
Hurry up! There's the shuttle door!
[Shouting]

1296
01:22:31,976 --> 01:22:34,774
Fire's coming at us! Close the door now!

1297
01:22:40,018 --> 01:22:41,986
Go! Go! Go!

1298
01:22:49,127 --> 01:22:53,723
Freedom, the Independence crew
is on board and accounted for.

1299
01:22:53,798 --> 01:22:57,825
- We're even heavy one cosmonaut.
- They got 90 percent of their fuel.

1300
01:22:57,902 --> 01:22:59,961
Pretty intense, huh?

1301
01:23:00,038 --> 01:23:03,337
That's why I told you, "Touch nothing. "

1302
01:23:03,408 --> 01:23:05,535
But you're bunch of cowboys.

1303
01:23:09,914 --> 01:23:12,644
So while the consciousness
of the planet is unified,

1304
01:23:12,717 --> 01:23:16,483
focused on the NASA mission taking place
right now in the vast ocean of space,

1305
01:23:16,554 --> 01:23:19,489
- [Speaking Russian]
- We're now in the final hours of the mission,

1306
01:23:19,557 --> 01:23:22,651
as the Freedom and Independence
prepare to slingshot around the moon.

1307
01:23:31,169 --> 01:23:34,832
Morning, guys. It's time
to suit up, I guess.

1308
01:23:34,906 --> 01:23:36,840
Uh, we got a big day.

1309
01:23:36,908 --> 01:23:40,708
- Eighteen seconds to radio interrupt.
- Booster sequence confirmed.

1310
01:23:40,778 --> 01:23:43,872
This is Houston.
Roger that, Freedom. We copy.

1311
01:23:43,948 --> 01:23:46,178
Shuttles are ready
for the burn around the moon.

1312
01:23:46,251 --> 01:23:48,515
Radio contact terminated. We're out.

1313
01:23:48,586 --> 01:23:53,285
Nine and a half Gs for 11 minutes.
I'd start praying about right now.

1314
01:23:58,463 --> 01:24:01,193
So this is the part
where we're supposed to just...

1315
01:24:01,266 --> 01:24:03,894
hold on real tight and, uh,
hope we don't die.

1316
01:24:03,968 --> 01:24:07,404
- Stand by for lunar roll.
- High inclination. Lunar orbit.

1317
01:24:09,574 --> 01:24:12,304
You boys got those wills
filled out correctly?

1318
01:24:27,825 --> 01:24:31,283
All right, men, this is what
we trained for. Now just suck it up!

1319
01:24:31,362 --> 01:24:34,195
On the mark. Five. Four.

1320
01:24:34,265 --> 01:24:36,859
Three. Two. One.

1321
01:24:47,412 --> 01:24:50,006
- Is this supposed to be like this?
- Don't worry. This is normal.

1322
01:24:50,081 --> 01:24:52,015
How would you know?
[Groaning]

1323
01:24:52,083 --> 01:24:54,517
- Fourteen thousand miles an hour.
- Four Gs.

1324
01:24:54,585 --> 01:24:57,748
- Ahh! - How long does
this last? - Six Gs.

1325
01:25:00,792 --> 01:25:04,057
- Fifteen thousand. - Really
heavy, man! - This isn't normal.

1326
01:25:04,128 --> 01:25:06,528
- What do you mean, "this isn't normal"?
- This is way worse!

1327
01:25:06,597 --> 01:25:08,758
Eight Gs. Hang tight!

1328
01:25:08,833 --> 01:25:13,361
We're not gonna make it!
Oh, we're gonna die!

1329
01:25:13,438 --> 01:25:15,702
Twelve minutes. Flight,
we still got nothin' here.

1330
01:25:15,773 --> 01:25:19,607
- [All Groaning]
- This is too fast!

1331
01:25:23,881 --> 01:25:27,817
- Ten Gs!
- [Groaning Continues]

1332
01:25:34,926 --> 01:25:37,952
- [Groaning]
- [Laughing]

1333
01:25:38,029 --> 01:25:42,989
[Sharp]
We're maxed at 22,500!

1334
01:25:43,067 --> 01:25:46,002
- [Groaning]
- [Rattling Ceases]

1335
01:25:47,405 --> 01:25:49,339
[Exhales]

1336
01:25:51,275 --> 01:25:54,904
We have acquisition of signal
from Independence and Freedom.

1337
01:25:54,979 --> 01:25:58,415
- [Relieved Chattering]
- We're in, guys. All right. Welcome back, team.

1338
01:25:58,483 --> 01:26:00,815
We have visual of the target, Houston.

1339
01:26:09,894 --> 01:26:12,260
You see that?

1340
01:26:16,467 --> 01:26:20,528
- Wow.
- [Computer Blipping]

1341
01:26:20,605 --> 01:26:24,132
- Come in, Independence.
- [Sharp] Houston, you gotta see this to believe it.

1342
01:26:27,111 --> 01:26:30,740
Okay, team, let's take 'em in. Okay,
Quincy, how much tail debris do we have?

1343
01:26:30,815 --> 01:26:33,010
[Man] Freedom, turn on FOD radar.

1344
01:26:33,084 --> 01:26:35,752
- FOD radar on.
- [Blipping]

1345
01:26:35,885 --> 01:26:40,481
Everybody, hang on. This could get
a little rough. Engaging evasive radar.

1346
01:26:48,064 --> 01:26:50,589
Hold on!

1347
01:26:59,776 --> 01:27:03,041
Goddamn! We got debris!

1348
01:27:04,647 --> 01:27:07,013
[Watts]
We're dumping auxiliary boosters.

1349
01:27:20,396 --> 01:27:23,490
- Houston, do you read me?
- We got debris!

1350
01:27:26,302 --> 01:27:31,638
We're goin' in! We're comin' in hot!

1351
01:27:31,707 --> 01:27:35,040
Independence, try to maintain your
present heading. You've got a target L.Z.

1352
01:27:35,111 --> 01:27:38,308
- There's too much debris! We gotta peel off!
- Negative!

1353
01:27:40,283 --> 01:27:42,843
- [Loud Crashing]
- We're hit!

1354
01:27:45,988 --> 01:27:49,048
- Mayday, mayday!
- I've lost main thrusters. Get 'em back up!

1355
01:27:49,125 --> 01:27:51,491
Mayday, Houston, mayday!
We've lost R.C.S. Thrusters!

1356
01:27:51,561 --> 01:27:55,588
Mayday, Freedom, mayday! We are
out of control! We are going down!

1357
01:27:55,665 --> 01:27:58,031
Do you read me?
Freedom, we are going down!

1358
01:28:04,340 --> 01:28:08,538
- [All Shouting]
- [Thrusters Roaring]

1359
01:28:11,180 --> 01:28:13,375
- We're gonna hit!
- [Blipping]

1360
01:28:22,725 --> 01:28:26,957
Everybody, go to your own life support!
Lock yourself in the cargo bay!

1361
01:28:28,831 --> 01:28:33,859
We are going down! Houston! Houston,
we are going down! We have lost control!

1362
01:28:33,936 --> 01:28:36,564
I can't get it on!

1363
01:28:38,007 --> 01:28:41,340
- Good luck, Freedom.
- Oh, my God, this is it.

1364
01:28:44,046 --> 01:28:46,378
- [Blipping]
- [All Screaming]

1365
01:28:57,460 --> 01:29:02,159
[Lev Shouting In Russian]

1366
01:29:19,882 --> 01:29:22,350
[Screams]

1367
01:29:31,727 --> 01:29:34,594
Sharp, what the hell is that?
Is that the Independence?

1368
01:29:40,469 --> 01:29:43,927
[Sharp] Houston, Independence is
a dead stick. They're not gonna make it.

1369
01:29:56,886 --> 01:29:59,377
Houston, Independence has gone down.

1370
01:30:11,367 --> 01:30:13,835
When I touch this baby down,
full reverse thrust.

1371
01:30:13,903 --> 01:30:16,997
- Fires on your right, Sharp! - Reversing
the thrusters! - [Thrusters Roaring]

1372
01:30:18,074 --> 01:30:20,634
Hang tight! Hang tight!

1373
01:30:20,710 --> 01:30:24,271
Houston, we overshot our landing field.
We overshot our landing field.

1374
01:30:24,347 --> 01:30:26,338
Oh, no!

1375
01:30:31,520 --> 01:30:35,388
- [Grunting]
- [Ice Smashing]

1376
01:30:39,695 --> 01:30:41,526
[Shouting]

1377
01:30:46,535 --> 01:30:48,935
- God!
- Aah!

1378
01:30:51,841 --> 01:30:54,776
- [Crashing Stops]
- [Whimpering, Panting]

1379
01:30:57,213 --> 01:31:00,979
- [Whimpering]
- [Panting]

1380
01:31:03,252 --> 01:31:07,655
Initiate system light system check. Make
sure we can still get off this rock.

1381
01:31:07,723 --> 01:31:11,716
Our electrical system is screwed.
I'm going to back-up. Fuel seals check.

1382
01:31:11,794 --> 01:31:15,821
- Engine seals check. Pressure seals check.
- Oh, God. Oh!

1383
01:31:18,234 --> 01:31:23,262
- Anyone hurt?
- [Panting] Where's...

1384
01:31:23,339 --> 01:31:27,469
Where's the other shuttle?
What happened to the other shuttle?

1385
01:31:27,543 --> 01:31:30,671
- Independence is off the grid.
- "Off the grid"?

1386
01:31:30,746 --> 01:31:33,442
What are you, a freakin' cyborg?
What does that mean?

1387
01:31:33,516 --> 01:31:36,246
Hey, you saw it yourself, right?

1388
01:31:36,318 --> 01:31:38,286
They're gone.

1389
01:31:38,354 --> 01:31:43,223
Come in, Freedom. This is
CAPCOM Houston. Freedom, come in.

1390
01:31:43,292 --> 01:31:46,693
This is CAPCOM Houston.
Come in, Freedom.

1391
01:31:46,762 --> 01:31:50,425
- God!
- Let's just ask God to take care of our friends.

1392
01:31:52,435 --> 01:31:57,668
- May they rest in peace.
- Amen.

1393
01:31:57,740 --> 01:32:00,538
[Computers Blipping]

1394
01:32:04,680 --> 01:32:08,138
- We got eight hours.
- [Gasps]

1395
01:32:08,217 --> 01:32:10,447
Let's get this job done and go home.

1396
01:32:10,519 --> 01:32:12,487
Nothin'.

1397
01:32:12,555 --> 01:32:15,854
Come on, Watts, Sharp, somebody.

1398
01:32:15,925 --> 01:32:18,792
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1399
01:32:18,861 --> 01:32:23,798
Come in, Freedom. Freedom, come in.
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1400
01:32:23,866 --> 01:32:29,031
- Maybe you shouldn't be here.
- I don't have anywhere else to go.

1401
01:32:29,105 --> 01:32:31,300
Freedom, come in.
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1402
01:32:33,175 --> 01:32:36,110
All right, let's get the tools
unpacked and fire up the Armadillo.

1403
01:32:36,178 --> 01:32:39,306
- We're not getting a damn thing on the inertial nav system.
- I know where we are.

1404
01:32:39,381 --> 01:32:42,179
Please step away.
Radio signal's dead.

1405
01:32:42,251 --> 01:32:44,185
I'm flipping the backup generator.

1406
01:32:44,253 --> 01:32:46,653
Radio signal's gonna be cut in half
till we get main power back.

1407
01:32:46,722 --> 01:32:52,251
We're in segment 202, lateral grid 9,
site 15H-32, give or take a few yards.

1408
01:32:52,328 --> 01:32:57,163
- Captain America here blew the landing by 26 miles.
- How the hell do you know that?

1409
01:32:57,233 --> 01:33:00,999
- Because I'm a genius.
- The gauges will not read.

1410
01:33:01,070 --> 01:33:03,698
They're all peaked, like
we're plugged into some magnetic field.

1411
01:33:03,772 --> 01:33:06,297
- Well, who on this spaceship wants to know why?
- [Sharp] By all means.

1412
01:33:06,375 --> 01:33:08,843
The reason we were shooting
for grid 8 is because...

1413
01:33:08,911 --> 01:33:12,074
thermographics indicated that
grid 9 was compressed iron ferrite.

1414
01:33:13,482 --> 01:33:16,383
Which means that you landed us
on a goddamn iron plate.

1415
01:33:19,889 --> 01:33:22,323
All right. Well, you heard the man.
Let's wheel out the remote satellite link.

1416
01:33:22,391 --> 01:33:26,463
- We need that radio.
- Oh, God, please tell me we still got one of 'em.

1417
01:33:26,596 --> 01:33:29,759
- [Computers Beeping]
- [Man] Independence has flat-lined.

1418
01:33:29,833 --> 01:33:32,301
[Weeping]

1419
01:33:59,162 --> 01:34:02,097
[Sighs, Grunting]

1420
01:34:10,807 --> 01:34:13,901
Oh. Oh.

1421
01:34:13,977 --> 01:34:16,741
Oscar! Oscar!

1422
01:34:20,283 --> 01:34:22,217
Oh, God!

1423
01:34:24,521 --> 01:34:26,512
Hello! Anyone!

1424
01:34:26,589 --> 01:34:31,185
Is anyone else alive?
Somebody, help me!

1425
01:34:32,962 --> 01:34:35,795
A.J.!

1426
01:34:35,865 --> 01:34:39,096
- Where are you?
- I'm here.

1427
01:34:39,168 --> 01:34:42,262
[Grunting]

1428
01:34:42,338 --> 01:34:46,274
Lev, there's no one else.

1429
01:34:46,342 --> 01:34:49,311
- There's no one else.
- I know.

1430
01:34:49,379 --> 01:34:52,007
[Bear] Oh, man.

1431
01:34:52,081 --> 01:34:55,141
- [A.J.] Bear, where are you?
- [Bear] A.J.? A.J.?

1432
01:34:56,686 --> 01:34:59,621
- [Bear] I'm in the shuttle, man.
- [Grunts]

1433
01:34:59,689 --> 01:35:03,648
- Are you all right?
- I'm so glad to see you, man.

1434
01:35:03,726 --> 01:35:07,753
I never thought I'd be so happy
to see your ugly face.

1435
01:35:07,830 --> 01:35:12,096
- Houston, do you read? This is Freedom.
- [Sharp] Check your thrusters.

1436
01:35:12,168 --> 01:35:15,934
- [Watts] Houston, do you copy?
- [Sharp] Is everyone good to go?

1437
01:35:25,949 --> 01:35:27,883
Wow.

1438
01:35:37,226 --> 01:35:41,322
[Harry] Down here! In the valley!

1439
01:35:41,397 --> 01:35:44,161
This place is like
Dr. Seuss's worst nightmare.

1440
01:35:44,233 --> 01:35:49,193
Let's get the remote satellite.
We'll get better reception up there.

1441
01:35:49,272 --> 01:35:52,571
[Harry] Bring Max down.
Watch yourself through here, Max.

1442
01:35:52,642 --> 01:35:56,009
- There're a couple big fissures.
- To the left!

1443
01:35:56,079 --> 01:35:59,344
Bring it to the left!

1444
01:36:02,652 --> 01:36:05,780
[Harry] Rockhound, you come on down here
and take some readings down in the flat spot.

1445
01:36:05,855 --> 01:36:09,814
- [Beeping]
- Iron ferrite.

1446
01:36:13,563 --> 01:36:18,091
- I have fire.
- [Harry] Watts, I'm comin' back. Stand by.

1447
01:36:18,167 --> 01:36:22,160
- Mostly iron, Rockhound.
- God, I hate knowing everything.

1448
01:36:22,238 --> 01:36:25,230
We couldn't have picked
a worse spot to drill.

1449
01:36:25,308 --> 01:36:29,301
Well, I can pretty much guarantee
it's not gonna be thicker than 50 feet.

1450
01:36:29,379 --> 01:36:32,314
- How do you figure that?
- 'Cause if it is, we're screwed.

1451
01:36:34,651 --> 01:36:37,279
- Max, you good?
- Yeah. Just makin' hole.

1452
01:36:37,353 --> 01:36:40,584
- Turn it around.
- [Max] Friggin' outer space.

1453
01:36:42,725 --> 01:36:44,818
It's good.

1454
01:36:51,701 --> 01:36:55,330
All right. We're in. Another light.
We're cuttin' through pretty good.

1455
01:36:55,405 --> 01:36:58,841
There's some stuff in here
I ain't never seen.

1456
01:36:58,908 --> 01:37:01,968
- All right, let's punch it down!
- [Metal Creaking]

1457
01:37:02,045 --> 01:37:05,572
- Hey, Harry, did you see that?
- Yeah, Max, I see it. I see it. What is it?

1458
01:37:05,648 --> 01:37:07,912
- We lost the bite in the bit.
- All right. Back it off. Back it off.

1459
01:37:07,984 --> 01:37:10,248
Goddamn it!

1460
01:37:10,319 --> 01:37:14,847
Sounds like we twisted a shank. Back it out
of there, Max. Good. Good. Hold 'er there.

1461
01:37:18,194 --> 01:37:22,028
Wow, this is a goddamn Greek tragedy.

1462
01:37:22,098 --> 01:37:26,194
- We've all seen broken drill heads before.
- Not after ten feet.

1463
01:37:26,269 --> 01:37:29,261
- I never seen one.
- Well, now you've seen one.

1464
01:37:29,338 --> 01:37:31,772
- What do you want?
- Unpack the Judge.

1465
01:37:34,243 --> 01:37:36,438
[A.J.] Bear, Lev.

1466
01:37:36,512 --> 01:37:39,811
[Lev]
We're only three astronauts left now.

1467
01:37:39,882 --> 01:37:43,716
[A.J.] We're not astronauts. We're oil
drillers. We're not even supposed to be here.

1468
01:37:43,786 --> 01:37:46,983
What? You're not astronaut?

1469
01:37:47,056 --> 01:37:49,354
I'm getting us outta here. Get in.

1470
01:37:49,425 --> 01:37:51,893
- Why?
- Just get in the Armadillo. I have an idea.

1471
01:37:51,961 --> 01:37:54,327
Houston, this is Freedom.
Do you copy?

1472
01:37:54,397 --> 01:37:56,957
Houston, do you copy?
Freedom shuttle has...

1473
01:37:57,033 --> 01:38:00,400
- [Radio Static Hissing]
- We're gettin' some scattered video feeds here.

1474
01:38:00,470 --> 01:38:03,735
[Watts]
Houston, this is Freedom. Do you copy?

1475
01:38:03,806 --> 01:38:06,366
- Thank God we have you, Freedom.
- Freedom, this is Houston. Go ahead.

1476
01:38:06,442 --> 01:38:09,377
- Don't lose 'em, Malloy.
- Sharp, I'm getting something.

1477
01:38:09,445 --> 01:38:12,437
- Houston, this is Freedom. We have landed safely.
- Where are they?

1478
01:38:12,515 --> 01:38:14,881
We are at site coordinates
approximately 15H-32...

1479
01:38:14,951 --> 01:38:16,942
- Okay, I want to know everything we can about that location.
- Got it.

1480
01:38:17,019 --> 01:38:19,817
- Get it before we lose 'em.
- We're also having electric and antenna difficulties.

1481
01:38:19,889 --> 01:38:23,484
- Walter, get Mechanical on that.
- But we have commenced drilling.

1482
01:38:23,559 --> 01:38:26,289
- Stevens, we're losin' him. Bring it up on four. On four.
- Come on.

1483
01:38:26,362 --> 01:38:29,263
Shuttle flight capability not yet known.

1484
01:38:29,332 --> 01:38:31,459
- Bump the signal. -
Bumping. - Houston. Houston.

1485
01:38:31,534 --> 01:38:34,367
We lost 'em. Get 'em back.
Gruber, we need that hookup.

1486
01:38:36,472 --> 01:38:39,032
Show you how we do things
where I come from.

1487
01:38:47,183 --> 01:38:49,515
- Hold on!
- [Metal Crumpling]

1488
01:38:57,493 --> 01:38:59,518
Seat it.

1489
01:38:59,595 --> 01:39:02,792
All right, get ready.
Max, thread it.

1490
01:39:04,433 --> 01:39:07,596
Guys, the clock is tickin'.
Let's go, go, go, go, go!

1491
01:39:07,670 --> 01:39:10,400
All right! Good! Crank it loose!

1492
01:39:10,473 --> 01:39:13,101
Keep it at 25. Let's kick
a little asteroid butt!

1493
01:39:13,176 --> 01:39:15,201
All right, Chick. Give me
more torque on the turbine, huh?

1494
01:39:15,278 --> 01:39:18,076
- [Drill Whining]
- [Harry] Max, I need some more power down here!

1495
01:39:18,147 --> 01:39:20,615
- All right, boss.
- Throw it in fourth, then drop the hammer.

1496
01:39:20,683 --> 01:39:23,277
- Let's drill through this turd.
- [Harry] Come on, boys.

1497
01:39:23,352 --> 01:39:28,221
We gotta hop. We're fallin' behind.
Dig, dig, dig. Chew this iron bitch up.

1498
01:39:28,291 --> 01:39:32,990
[Metal Whining]

1499
01:39:33,062 --> 01:39:34,996
- Chick, the tranny's stuck.
- Harry!

1500
01:39:35,064 --> 01:39:38,124
- What is it?
- Chick, come on! Help!

1501
01:39:38,201 --> 01:39:40,362
- Release the clutch!
- Pull it up!

1502
01:39:40,436 --> 01:39:43,303
Okay. Well, this thing's not movin'.

1503
01:39:43,372 --> 01:39:45,636
No, no, no! Shut it down! Shut it...

1504
01:39:47,810 --> 01:39:52,679
[Groaning]

1505
01:39:52,748 --> 01:39:55,478
This is not workin' out, Harry.

1506
01:39:55,551 --> 01:40:00,488
- Oh, are you all right?
- Oh, blew the tranny. Blew the tranny.

1507
01:40:00,556 --> 01:40:03,525
Come on, God.

1508
01:40:03,593 --> 01:40:07,029
Just a little help.
That's all I'm askin'.

1509
01:40:07,096 --> 01:40:09,564
I think we're close enough.
He might've heard ya.

1510
01:40:13,336 --> 01:40:16,533
Here's the bad news. Before
the asteroid passed the moon,

1511
01:40:16,606 --> 01:40:18,938
her rotation was stable
at 32 degrees on an x axis.

1512
01:40:19,008 --> 01:40:23,576
But now look at this. The lunar
gravity's put her in a spin.

1513
01:40:23,645 --> 01:40:27,012
She's tumbling on all three axes.
This wasn't expected, sir.

1514
01:40:27,082 --> 01:40:29,812
- What does this do for communications?
- Not good.

1515
01:40:29,885 --> 01:40:33,116
We'll have definite contact with
the shuttle for only seven more minutes.

1516
01:40:33,188 --> 01:40:34,985
- After that it's radio darkness.
- For how long?

1517
01:40:35,057 --> 01:40:38,390
And after seven minutes,
we may never hear from them again.

1518
01:40:38,460 --> 01:40:41,020
But we're trying
to bounce a signal...

1519
01:40:41,096 --> 01:40:43,564
off a Russian military satellite,
reestablish contact that way.

1520
01:40:43,632 --> 01:40:48,035
If we lose the shuttle com, when do we lose
the ability to remote detonate that nuke?

1521
01:40:48,103 --> 01:40:50,697
The weapon remote receives a signal
from a Milstar satellite.

1522
01:40:50,773 --> 01:40:52,707
Higher orbit, more powerful transmitter.

1523
01:40:52,775 --> 01:40:57,212
If we've got the shuttle for seven minutes,
we can remote detonate for an additional five.

1524
01:40:57,279 --> 01:40:59,304
What he's trying to say, General,
is that, uh, in 12 minutes' time,

1525
01:40:59,381 --> 01:41:03,078
you may lose the ability
to detonate the nuke... permanently.

1526
01:41:03,152 --> 01:41:05,279
I've got to inform the president.

1527
01:41:05,354 --> 01:41:09,313
Just want to make sure you know
we're stuck on an asteroid.

1528
01:41:09,391 --> 01:41:11,325
- Do you know what you're doing now?
- No, no.

1529
01:41:11,393 --> 01:41:14,624
You know what? I have no idea
what I'm doing. I have no idea.

1530
01:41:14,696 --> 01:41:16,960
This button... I don't know
what that does, okay?

1531
01:41:17,032 --> 01:41:19,626
All I know is that
we just crashed back there,

1532
01:41:19,701 --> 01:41:22,602
I lost two of my friends,
we're 25 miles from Harry's shuttle.

1533
01:41:22,671 --> 01:41:26,198
We don't know if he's alive. We don't know if
he can fly. All I know is, there's a beep...

1534
01:41:26,275 --> 01:41:28,505
on this thing and I'm
trying to get us there.

1535
01:41:34,750 --> 01:41:36,684
[Beeping]

1536
01:41:36,752 --> 01:41:39,812
Let's get it unpacked.

1537
01:41:39,888 --> 01:41:43,585
- What's up?
- We're drilling through some kind of metal I've never seen before.

1538
01:41:43,659 --> 01:41:46,628
It's fried two of our drill bits,
and now we blew our first transmission.

1539
01:41:46,695 --> 01:41:49,630
- So how deep are we?
- We could use your help with the transmission, Colonel.

1540
01:41:49,698 --> 01:41:52,633
I have an assessment report due now.
We're supposed to be at 200 feet.

1541
01:41:52,701 --> 01:41:55,761
- So how deep are we?
- Not as deep as we'll be...

1542
01:41:55,838 --> 01:41:58,500
when you quit askin' me these questions
and help us load this transmission on.

1543
01:41:58,574 --> 01:42:02,066
- What is our current depth?
- Our current depth is not important, Colonel.

1544
01:42:02,144 --> 01:42:04,772
I'll decide what's important.
We've got 800 feet to drill.

1545
01:42:04,847 --> 01:42:07,816
You've had two and a half hours.
Where are we?

1546
01:42:09,685 --> 01:42:11,676
We're at 57 feet.

1547
01:42:11,753 --> 01:42:15,689
Now, if you're not too busy, maybe you
can give us a hand with this transmission.

1548
01:42:15,757 --> 01:42:20,990
Colonel Sharp! Get this strapped up.
I'll be right back. Colonel Sharp!

1549
01:42:21,063 --> 01:42:24,123
All right. I'm coming through.
We have contact. Over.

1550
01:42:24,199 --> 01:42:27,134
That's as clear as it's gonna get.

1551
01:42:27,202 --> 01:42:29,500
Houston, this is Freedom. Do you copy?

1552
01:42:29,571 --> 01:42:33,803
Working at a remote satellite link
at this moment. Transmission change.

1553
01:42:33,876 --> 01:42:36,538
- Colonel!
- Twenty minutes. Puts drilling final at ten hours.

1554
01:42:36,612 --> 01:42:40,378
Please advise. That's four hours
past the zero barrier. Please advise.

1555
01:42:40,449 --> 01:42:43,418
What the hell is this? "Zero depth"?

1556
01:42:43,485 --> 01:42:46,113
And where'd this come from?
Who are you talkin' to? Is that Truman?

1557
01:42:46,188 --> 01:42:50,648
Lemme have that phone. Gimme the phone. Truman!
Look, this is what happens when you drill.

1558
01:42:50,726 --> 01:42:54,787
We cannot use your "U.S. Air Force
Personnel Only" drill time card.

1559
01:42:54,863 --> 01:42:57,559
- Who wrote this thing, by the way?
- We're losing coms again.

1560
01:42:57,633 --> 01:42:59,601
Look... Is he getting this? Does he
hear me or... What's wrong with this?

1561
01:42:59,668 --> 01:43:02,364
- The com's down.
- What do you mean, "the com's down"?

1562
01:43:02,437 --> 01:43:04,769
[Sharp] What do I mean? I mean we've
lost communication to mission control.

1563
01:43:04,840 --> 01:43:07,536
Fine. Let's go back to the cargo bay
and get the transmission...

1564
01:43:07,609 --> 01:43:10,339
Harry, guess what. You had your shot.
You didn't do it. You understand me?

1565
01:43:10,412 --> 01:43:15,008
- You can't...
- Why don't you stay here... [Shouting]

1566
01:43:15,083 --> 01:43:19,076
Write a report, why don't ya?
That'll be... [Shouting Continues]

1567
01:43:19,154 --> 01:43:21,179
My men and I will go
and get this hole dug!

1568
01:43:21,256 --> 01:43:25,056
You and your men are the biggest
mistake in the history of NASA.

1569
01:43:26,962 --> 01:43:29,988
- [Man] We've lost communication.
- Oh, God.

1570
01:43:32,734 --> 01:43:37,569
- We're not lookin' too good right now.
- No shit.

1571
01:43:37,639 --> 01:43:40,267
We gotta get that radio back up.

1572
01:43:42,210 --> 01:43:45,236
[Man] Mr. President,
it's time to make a decision.

1573
01:43:45,314 --> 01:43:50,081
We can remote detonate the bomb
for only another five minutes.

1574
01:43:50,152 --> 01:43:55,852
- [Rings]
- Yes? Kimsey here. Yes, Mr. President.

1575
01:43:55,924 --> 01:43:57,892
Yes, we saw that too, sir.

1576
01:43:57,960 --> 01:44:00,861
But maybe we should wait until they...

1577
01:44:07,803 --> 01:44:10,966
Dan, get them out of there.

1578
01:44:11,039 --> 01:44:13,974
- Evac right now.
- What's goin' on here?

1579
01:44:14,042 --> 01:44:16,203
I've been ordered
to override the system.

1580
01:44:16,278 --> 01:44:20,908
[Elevator Bells Dinging]

1581
01:44:20,983 --> 01:44:23,349
Well, what is this?

1582
01:44:27,522 --> 01:44:30,184
Secondary protocol.

1583
01:44:35,430 --> 01:44:37,523
But they haven't drilled
the damn hole yet!

1584
01:44:42,437 --> 01:44:44,598
The president's advisors feel
that the drilling isn't working.

1585
01:44:44,673 --> 01:44:46,470
And we've lost radio contact,
maybe for good.

1586
01:44:46,541 --> 01:44:49,567
We've only got a few minutes left of
guaranteed ability to remote detonate that nuke.

1587
01:44:49,644 --> 01:44:52,545
If we don't do it now we could lose
control, and we may never get it back.

1588
01:44:52,614 --> 01:44:55,549
Well, you tell the president that
he better fire his so-called advisors.

1589
01:44:55,617 --> 01:44:59,018
If you detonate that nuke on the
surface, we waste a perfectly good bomb,

1590
01:44:59,087 --> 01:45:01,146
and we have one chance
to save this planet!

1591
01:45:01,223 --> 01:45:03,350
[Beeping]

1592
01:45:12,067 --> 01:45:17,437
- I need that radio. Gruber, give me everything you got now!
- [Gruber] Roger that.

1593
01:45:21,243 --> 01:45:24,542
Yes, Mr. President, I understand that
completely, but my point is very, very simple.

1594
01:45:24,613 --> 01:45:27,138
And I think you need to trust me on this
because I know something about it.

1595
01:45:27,215 --> 01:45:30,309
I guarantee you,
if you do this, you kill us all.

1596
01:45:34,056 --> 01:45:36,354
Yes, sir.

1597
01:45:36,425 --> 01:45:38,689
General, he wants you.

1598
01:45:40,796 --> 01:45:43,856
This is Kimsey. Yes, sir.

1599
01:45:43,932 --> 01:45:46,423
I understand.

1600
01:45:48,503 --> 01:45:51,438
The orders are
to remote detonate in 30 seconds.

1601
01:45:51,506 --> 01:45:55,067
You have not told them yet!

1602
01:45:55,143 --> 01:45:57,668
That is my father up there!

1603
01:45:57,746 --> 01:46:01,113
This is one order you shouldn't
follow, and you fucking know it!

1604
01:46:01,183 --> 01:46:03,879
Let her go. Let her go!

1605
01:46:05,020 --> 01:46:07,147
Your key, sir.

1606
01:46:09,791 --> 01:46:13,728
- [Consoles Beeping]
- God be with them.

1607
01:46:13,861 --> 01:46:16,557
Slow it down.

1608
01:46:16,630 --> 01:46:20,066
[Beeping]

1609
01:46:20,134 --> 01:46:23,570
[Timer Beeping]

1610
01:46:23,637 --> 01:46:25,605
Harry...

1611
01:46:25,673 --> 01:46:29,234
the clock on that
nine-foot nuclear weapon is ticking.

1612
01:46:30,611 --> 01:46:34,047
Oh, my God! Sharp!
Get back here now!

1613
01:46:35,449 --> 01:46:37,679
What? Get the shuttle ready to evac now!

1614
01:46:37,752 --> 01:46:40,414
- It just came on all by itself. What the hell's happening?
- Secondary protocol.

1615
01:46:40,488 --> 01:46:42,456
- What's that? What?
- Secondary protocol.

1616
01:46:42,523 --> 01:46:44,320
- What does that mean?
- What the hell's secondary protocol?

1617
01:46:44,391 --> 01:46:46,291
- They're detonating this thing from Earth.
- What do you mean, detonating?

1618
01:46:46,360 --> 01:46:48,157
- We haven't even drilled the hole yet!
- We'll drop it in the hole.

1619
01:46:48,229 --> 01:46:50,322
- What're you talkin' about? - The hole?
Whoa, whoa! - Get your helmets on now!

1620
01:46:50,397 --> 01:46:53,423
- Oh, no, no. How-How you turn it off?
- I got two men out on that rock!

1621
01:46:53,501 --> 01:46:55,833
I got a man out there too.
We gotta evac now.

1622
01:46:55,903 --> 01:46:57,837
Max, Rockhound, get back
to the shuttle, double-time!

1623
01:46:57,905 --> 01:47:00,840
- They could be on their way here.
- They're not on their way here.

1624
01:47:00,908 --> 01:47:03,672
They would've talked to us
by now. We would've seen them.

1625
01:47:03,744 --> 01:47:06,907
- Watts, air lock the cockpit now!
- I copy you.

1626
01:47:06,981 --> 01:47:10,280
- Max, Rockhound!
- Hey, wait a minute! How do you turn this thing off?

1627
01:47:10,351 --> 01:47:13,787
- [Radio Static Hissing] - Harry,
do you copy? - Somethin's wrong.

1628
01:47:13,854 --> 01:47:16,584
Yeah, it's all wrong, man.
We shouldn't even be up here.

1629
01:47:16,657 --> 01:47:18,682
I know. Let's go back to the ship!

1630
01:47:18,759 --> 01:47:21,421
I'm not leavin' without my men, Sharp.

1631
01:47:21,495 --> 01:47:24,692
We've got two and a half minutes
to drop it and get off this rock.

1632
01:47:24,765 --> 01:47:27,097
If they're not back by the time
we finish, we leave without 'em.

1633
01:47:27,168 --> 01:47:29,602
Okay, let's simplify this.
Let's just turn the bomb off right now.

1634
01:47:29,670 --> 01:47:32,503
If we don't put this bomb down
in a hole 800 feet onto a fault line,

1635
01:47:32,573 --> 01:47:34,803
all you're gonna have is
a real expensive fireworks show.

1636
01:47:34,875 --> 01:47:37,435
This is turnin' into
a surrealistic nightmare here.

1637
01:47:37,511 --> 01:47:39,945
Watsler, are you listening? It's Truman.

1638
01:47:40,014 --> 01:47:44,007
Okay, listen to me carefully.
I want you to kill it. Kill the uplink.

1639
01:47:55,496 --> 01:47:59,159
- Give us the time, Sharp. Shut this bomb down now!
- It's not my call.

1640
01:47:59,233 --> 01:48:01,929
- Then whose call is it?
- An order to detonate can only come from the president.

1641
01:48:02,002 --> 01:48:03,902
- The president's not here! You've gotta give us more time!
- Let's just turn it off now.

1642
01:48:03,971 --> 01:48:05,996
I'm telling you
to shut this bomb down now!

1643
01:48:06,073 --> 01:48:08,041
- And I'm telling you it's not my call!
- Well, guess what.

1644
01:48:08,108 --> 01:48:10,941
- I just made the call for you.
- Harry!

1645
01:48:12,213 --> 01:48:16,047
Don't. You could set it off.

1646
01:48:16,116 --> 01:48:19,813
Oh, man. What're you doin'
with a gun in space?

1647
01:48:22,823 --> 01:48:27,658
Come on. Come on. We gotta stop
that bomb right now. Kill the uplink.

1648
01:48:27,728 --> 01:48:33,030
- This thing is gonna blow. We gotta get it off the ship.
- Easy.

1649
01:48:33,100 --> 01:48:38,504
- Stand down, Sergeant.
- Shut this bomb down and let us finish our job the right way.

1650
01:48:38,572 --> 01:48:40,699
I'm under orders to protect
a surface detonation.

1651
01:48:40,774 --> 01:48:44,972
I'm gonna give you three seconds to shut this
bomb down, and then I'm gonna make you shoot me.

1652
01:48:46,280 --> 01:48:48,612
Hurry, Watsler.
For Christ's sake, hurry.

1653
01:48:50,885 --> 01:48:53,513
- [Detonator Powering Down]
- What happened?

1654
01:48:55,656 --> 01:48:58,648
- Aah!
- [Grunting]

1655
01:48:58,726 --> 01:49:03,095
Sir, the override...
It's been overridden.

1656
01:49:03,163 --> 01:49:06,690
I bought us a couple of minutes, so get
that radio workin', okay? Hurry, hurry!

1657
01:49:06,767 --> 01:49:08,735
[Grunting]

1658
01:49:08,802 --> 01:49:12,966
Bring me all the way up here just to
blow me and my friends up? Is that it?

1659
01:49:13,040 --> 01:49:15,201
- [Gasping] Listen...
- Shut up!

1660
01:49:15,276 --> 01:49:19,713
Shut up, Colonel.
I'm talking now.

1661
01:49:19,780 --> 01:49:22,908
[Sharp] It could start again.
It might've been a warning.

1662
01:49:22,983 --> 01:49:24,917
- [Gasping]
- Uh-oh.

1663
01:49:24,985 --> 01:49:27,453
That's why you are gonna
dismantle this bomb.

1664
01:49:27,521 --> 01:49:30,490
All right. What'd we miss?

1665
01:49:34,261 --> 01:49:37,162
- Do it again.
- Go.

1666
01:49:39,633 --> 01:49:41,567
Keep tryin'.

1667
01:49:44,104 --> 01:49:49,007
Sir, I need you to cease and desist.
I need your terminal... now.

1668
01:49:51,845 --> 01:49:55,178
- They're reactivating the bomb.
- Comin' back on-line, sir.

1669
01:49:55,249 --> 01:49:58,184
- [Detonator Blipping]
- Oh, geez. Here we go again.

1670
01:49:58,252 --> 01:50:01,517
What're you doin' up here? And why did
you even bother to make the trip?

1671
01:50:01,588 --> 01:50:04,557
To do the right thing,
to see that it's done.

1672
01:50:04,625 --> 01:50:07,025
[Breathing Heavily]

1673
01:50:07,094 --> 01:50:10,222
[Gasping]

1674
01:50:11,632 --> 01:50:14,100
For God's sakes,
think about what you're doin'.

1675
01:50:14,168 --> 01:50:18,298
Why are you listenin' to someone
that's 100,000 miles away?

1676
01:50:18,372 --> 01:50:22,468
We're here.
Nobody down there can help us.

1677
01:50:22,543 --> 01:50:26,240
So if we don't get this job
done, then everybody's gone.

1678
01:50:26,313 --> 01:50:28,645
One minute.

1679
01:50:28,716 --> 01:50:31,583
I've been drillin' holes
in the earth for 30 years.

1680
01:50:31,652 --> 01:50:36,385
And I have never, never missed
a depth that I have aimed for.

1681
01:50:36,457 --> 01:50:39,858
And by God, I am not gonna miss
this one. I will make 800 feet.

1682
01:50:39,927 --> 01:50:45,490
- Forty-two seconds. - But I can't do
it alone, Colonel. I need your help.

1683
01:50:45,566 --> 01:50:49,662
You swear on your daughter's life,
on my family's,

1684
01:50:49,737 --> 01:50:51,671
that you can hit that mark?

1685
01:50:51,739 --> 01:50:56,767
I will make 800 feet.
I swear to God, I will.

1686
01:50:56,844 --> 01:50:59,836
Then let's turn this bomb off.

1687
01:50:59,913 --> 01:51:02,473
[Beeping]

1688
01:51:08,989 --> 01:51:11,048
[Beeping Continues]

1689
01:51:11,125 --> 01:51:14,925
Steady. Take it back. That's what you'll
have to do. Get 'em off backwards.

1690
01:51:14,995 --> 01:51:18,453
- Rainbow track? Under... Under one? Under... Okay.
- All of 'em. All of 'em.

1691
01:51:18,532 --> 01:51:21,990
- Okay. Are we free of static?
- Oh, do a good job. Do a good job.

1692
01:51:22,069 --> 01:51:24,037
- Steady. Steady.
- Good job. All right. All right.

1693
01:51:24,104 --> 01:51:27,505
Go! Go! Go! Red wire "A." Ready? And...

1694
01:51:27,574 --> 01:51:30,065
Now. Come on! Come on! Come on! Come on!

1695
01:51:30,144 --> 01:51:32,339
- [Breathing Heavily]
- Negative "B."

1696
01:51:32,413 --> 01:51:37,112
- Ready, and now. - Do a good job. Do
a good job. - Track flipped. Hots in.

1697
01:51:37,184 --> 01:51:39,675
- It better be. Go. - Red
or blue? - [Beeping Faster]

1698
01:51:40,888 --> 01:51:43,448
Re...

1699
01:51:44,992 --> 01:51:47,392
- [Whimpering]
- [Beeping Continues]

1700
01:51:47,461 --> 01:51:49,395
Blue.

1701
01:51:49,463 --> 01:51:51,727
[Beeping Stops]

1702
01:51:51,799 --> 01:51:53,733
Good job!

1703
01:51:53,801 --> 01:51:55,928
[All Panting]

1704
01:51:58,705 --> 01:52:01,976
Oh, God, it sucks up here.

1705
01:52:02,109 --> 01:52:05,408
- Sir, the clock has stopped at three seconds.
- What?

1706
01:52:05,479 --> 01:52:08,676
Have we lost complete radio contact?

1707
01:52:08,749 --> 01:52:11,513
I got some magic happening. We're
bouncing off Russian and French satellites.

1708
01:52:11,585 --> 01:52:15,248
- It may have a faint signal.
- Houston? Houston, do you copy?

1709
01:52:16,757 --> 01:52:19,123
Go ahead, Freedom.

1710
01:52:19,193 --> 01:52:22,321
Houston, you have a problem... Problem.

1711
01:52:22,396 --> 01:52:25,058
See, I promised my little girl
that I'd be comin' home.

1712
01:52:25,132 --> 01:52:31,002
Now, I don't know what you people are doin'
down there, but we got a hole to dig up there.

1713
01:52:31,071 --> 01:52:34,472
- [Cheering]
- Go, go, go, go! Come on. We got work to do.

1714
01:52:34,541 --> 01:52:38,409
Okay, guys. All go, no quit.
How ya doin' down there? Good?

1715
01:52:38,479 --> 01:52:41,380
Okay, got the tranny.
We're back in business.

1716
01:52:41,448 --> 01:52:44,884
Hey, you guys should take a break
and come up and see this.

1717
01:52:46,587 --> 01:52:49,385
Wow. Got a great view
of the Earth from here.

1718
01:52:49,456 --> 01:52:51,720
Too bad we'll never
set foot on her again.

1719
01:52:51,825 --> 01:52:54,020
- Lev, do you see anything?
- No.

1720
01:52:54,094 --> 01:52:56,085
Well, keep goin'.
I'm not givin' up.

1721
01:52:57,264 --> 01:52:59,425
Hold up here, Bear.

1722
01:52:59,500 --> 01:53:01,661
- [Lev] Oh, boy.
- [A.J.] This is great.

1723
01:53:01,735 --> 01:53:04,670
We just happen to run into
the Grand Canyon on the asteroid?

1724
01:53:04,738 --> 01:53:08,037
I told you, you took
a wrong way, a wrong road.

1725
01:53:08,108 --> 01:53:11,373
[A.J.] What-What road?
Do you see any roads around here?

1726
01:53:11,445 --> 01:53:15,541
[Lev] You know what? I do not have
much pleasure being near God's ear.

1727
01:53:15,616 --> 01:53:18,210
But you think this is
looking good, or what?

1728
01:53:18,285 --> 01:53:22,745
Lev, why don't you just do humanity
a favor and just shut the hell up?

1729
01:53:27,194 --> 01:53:29,628
Have you ever heard of Evel Knievel?

1730
01:53:29,696 --> 01:53:32,062
No, I never saw Star Wars.

1731
01:53:38,305 --> 01:53:40,796
All right. Doin' a good job.

1732
01:53:40,874 --> 01:53:43,342
- Give me a depth reading, Max.
- We're 150 feet, Harry.

1733
01:53:43,410 --> 01:53:48,643
¤ [Humming "William Tell Overture"]
Yee-ha!

1734
01:53:48,715 --> 01:53:52,446
Ride 'em, cowboy!
Yippee-kai-yo, kai-yay!

1735
01:53:52,519 --> 01:53:56,751
Get off... the nuclear... warhead.

1736
01:53:56,824 --> 01:53:58,849
I was doin' that guy
from that movie, you know,

1737
01:53:58,926 --> 01:54:02,054
Slim Pickens, where he rides it
all the way in... the nuclear warhead.

1738
01:54:02,129 --> 01:54:04,996
- Now.
- Oh, you didn't see that one, huh?

1739
01:54:05,065 --> 01:54:07,966
We got 700 feet of hole
to dig, Rockhound.

1740
01:54:08,035 --> 01:54:11,061
All right. Just- Just wanted to feel
the power between my legs, brother.

1741
01:54:13,273 --> 01:54:15,639
Hey, Sharp.

1742
01:54:15,709 --> 01:54:18,940
[Chanting]
No nukes! No nukes! No nukes!

1743
01:54:19,012 --> 01:54:21,037
You got any more bullets
in that gun, Sharp?

1744
01:54:21,115 --> 01:54:24,016
[A.J.] What did Watts tell you, Bear? If she
kicked you in the balls, you'd keep floating.

1745
01:54:24,084 --> 01:54:27,053
- Yeah.
- [Engine Roaring]

1746
01:54:27,121 --> 01:54:29,055
[A.J.] We turn the thrusters off,

1747
01:54:29,123 --> 01:54:31,557
we jump this thing,
we float right over it.

1748
01:54:31,625 --> 01:54:33,752
Go over it again, Lev.

1749
01:54:33,827 --> 01:54:38,696
- Throw the jet thrusters off exactly when we jump.
- Okay.

1750
01:54:38,765 --> 01:54:41,700
And then we're gonna put them on,
and we gonna go down nice and slow.

1751
01:54:41,768 --> 01:54:44,794
- That's it. That's it, baby. That's it.
- Is this gonna work?

1752
01:54:44,872 --> 01:54:48,933
- I don't know.
- Lev, you know what, just lie to me.

1753
01:54:49,009 --> 01:54:52,206
Let's say 50-50... No. More like, uh...

1754
01:54:52,279 --> 01:54:55,373
like 70-30 or 80-20.

1755
01:54:55,449 --> 01:55:00,477
But you know what? If it works, the two
of you gonna be heroes, just like me.

1756
01:55:00,554 --> 01:55:04,046
Screw it.
We're jumpin' over this canyon.

1757
01:55:07,161 --> 01:55:11,461
Just for the record,
this is a very bad idea!

1758
01:55:13,667 --> 01:55:16,830
- Wait for the edge. Don't hit it till we get there.
- I'm waiting.

1759
01:55:18,872 --> 01:55:21,841
- [Lev] Three.
- [A.J. Chattering]

1760
01:55:21,909 --> 01:55:24,377
[Lev] Two. One!

1761
01:55:24,444 --> 01:55:26,537
Aah!

1762
01:55:34,021 --> 01:55:37,252
- Yes! It's working!
- It's working!

1763
01:55:37,324 --> 01:55:40,782
- [Lev] Oh, my God!
- [All Shouting]

1764
01:55:40,861 --> 01:55:45,628
- I'm a genius! Wait a minute.
- Whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

1765
01:55:45,699 --> 01:55:47,997
- We got some rocks!
- Go left! Go left!

1766
01:55:48,068 --> 01:55:50,730
Lev, Lev, I can't do anything!

1767
01:55:50,804 --> 01:55:55,332
- [All Screaming]
- [Crashing]

1768
01:55:59,947 --> 01:56:02,939
Oh, okay, okay, we're
floating into outer space.

1769
01:56:03,016 --> 01:56:05,314
- Check main switch.
- Uh, this could be a little bit of a problem.

1770
01:56:06,687 --> 01:56:08,848
- Thrusters on... now!
- All right, turn 'em on.

1771
01:56:08,922 --> 01:56:12,688
- [Rattling]
- What's wrong?

1772
01:56:12,759 --> 01:56:17,253
I- I don't know. The-The thrusters
not working. I hate this machine!

1773
01:56:17,331 --> 01:56:19,799
- I thought you had this planned! What're we supposed to do?
- Be quiet! I must think!

1774
01:56:19,866 --> 01:56:22,960
- I'm stepping outside.
- You're-You're going outside?

1775
01:56:23,036 --> 01:56:28,599
I am the only certified astronaut,
and I'm saving your American ass!

1776
01:56:29,376 --> 01:56:31,776
[Grunts]

1777
01:56:31,845 --> 01:56:34,814
Yes. You'll listen to him. Right.

1778
01:56:39,953 --> 01:56:43,787
Hurry up, Lev, because
we're about a mile off the asteroid!

1779
01:56:43,857 --> 01:56:47,190
Just a second.
The fuel line is iced up.

1780
01:56:47,261 --> 01:56:51,630
- I think maybe workin' now.
- No, Lev, it's not working!

1781
01:56:51,698 --> 01:56:54,565
I'm sorry, A.J. I was way off the odds.

1782
01:56:54,635 --> 01:56:57,229
- [Bear] We're gettin' higher, man.
- Look out!

1783
01:56:57,304 --> 01:56:59,272
The rocks! Rocks are coming!

1784
01:56:59,339 --> 01:57:02,831
[Moaning, Grunting]

1785
01:57:06,146 --> 01:57:10,446
- Hold on!
- Aah!

1786
01:57:12,019 --> 01:57:14,510
- Pull the thrusters!
- Lev, look out!

1787
01:57:16,556 --> 01:57:19,024
[All Screaming]

1788
01:57:21,361 --> 01:57:24,353
- We lost Lev.
- A.J.! [Grunting]

1789
01:57:24,431 --> 01:57:27,923
- A.J., the thrusters!
- Aah!

1790
01:57:30,937 --> 01:57:33,098
Let's get Lev back!

1791
01:57:33,173 --> 01:57:37,769
- Aah!
- [Gasping]

1792
01:57:41,581 --> 01:57:44,015
Lev, hold on! We're comin' in!

1793
01:57:45,552 --> 01:57:47,747
[Grunting]

1794
01:57:51,958 --> 01:57:55,519
[Grunting]

1795
01:57:55,595 --> 01:58:00,498
[All Panting]

1796
01:58:00,567 --> 01:58:02,432
Thank You, Jesus. Thank You, Lord.

1797
01:58:02,502 --> 01:58:04,663
Thank You. Thank You,
thank You, thank You, thank You.

1798
01:58:04,738 --> 01:58:07,673
[Grunting] Lev!

1799
01:58:07,741 --> 01:58:13,236
- Now I'm really a Russian hero!
- I told you!

1800
01:58:13,313 --> 01:58:15,804
- I know!
- I knew this would work!

1801
01:58:15,882 --> 01:58:18,282
- Good odds, you know?
- Come on, Lev.

1802
01:58:18,352 --> 01:58:21,189
- Get in here. We gotta go.
- Yah!

1803
01:58:21,322 --> 01:58:24,348
[Rumbling]

1804
01:58:24,425 --> 01:58:26,757
Rockhound, keep on that transmission.

1805
01:58:26,827 --> 01:58:29,159
- Tranny looks good, Harry.
- All right. Take it outta there.

1806
01:58:29,230 --> 01:58:31,198
Lock it down, Chick.

1807
01:58:32,867 --> 01:58:36,496
Nice.

1808
01:58:36,571 --> 01:58:39,267
How come we didn't get
any training on this thing?

1809
01:58:39,340 --> 01:58:43,037
Whoa. Very cool. I could take out
this asteroid single-handedly.

1810
01:58:43,110 --> 01:58:46,602
- [Machine Whirring]
- Okay, boys, give it a rest. I'll take it from here.

1811
01:58:46,681 --> 01:58:49,479
- [Machine Gun Firing]
- Whoa!

1812
01:58:49,550 --> 01:58:52,041
- What the hell is that?
- It's Rockhound. - Whoa.

1813
01:58:52,119 --> 01:58:54,280
This is so much fun, it's freaky.

1814
01:58:56,224 --> 01:58:58,385
- Rockhound!
- [Cheering]

1815
01:58:58,459 --> 01:59:00,620
Whoa, watch your heads. Sorry, Harry.

1816
01:59:03,164 --> 01:59:05,962
- Outta my way, boys!
- Rockhound!

1817
01:59:06,033 --> 01:59:09,833
- Meet your maker, asteroid!
- [Both Grunting]

1818
01:59:13,007 --> 01:59:16,374
- What the hell's the matter with you, Rockhound? Goddamn!
- This is insane.

1819
01:59:16,444 --> 01:59:20,346
- Have you lost your mind? -
No. - He's got space dementia.

1820
01:59:20,414 --> 01:59:22,609
Harry, you want to watch your man.

1821
01:59:25,119 --> 01:59:30,352
Max, downshift and put it in reverse.
We gotta get that pipe outta there.

1822
01:59:30,424 --> 01:59:32,585
- [Max] Uh-oh.
- [Grunts]

1823
01:59:32,660 --> 01:59:35,060
[Loud Rumbling]

1824
01:59:35,129 --> 01:59:38,030
- What's happening? - The
ground's cracking! - Earthquake!

1825
01:59:46,340 --> 01:59:49,707
Quick, shut it off!

1826
01:59:49,777 --> 01:59:53,178
- Shut it off! Shut it off now!
- We're gonna have a blowout!

1827
01:59:53,247 --> 01:59:55,715
- We hit a gas pocket!
- We got pressure out the ass!

1828
01:59:55,783 --> 01:59:57,910
[Grunting]

1829
01:59:57,985 --> 02:00:01,887
Max, get your helmet on!
Max, she's gonna blow!

1830
02:00:01,956 --> 02:00:05,084
- Aah! Oh, Jesus, I'm cooking!
- Max, get outta there!

1831
02:00:05,159 --> 02:00:09,357
This is it! Harry!

1832
02:00:11,632 --> 02:00:13,657
I'm bailing!

1833
02:00:16,804 --> 02:00:18,328
Max!

1834
02:00:20,308 --> 02:00:22,435
Good-bye, Max.

1835
02:00:22,510 --> 02:00:25,877
- Max!
- Take care, buddy.

1836
02:00:25,946 --> 02:00:29,404
- Armadillo's off the scope. - I think we've
had a blowout. - No sign of the Armadillo.

1837
02:00:29,483 --> 02:00:31,644
[All Shouting]

1838
02:01:01,015 --> 02:01:04,314
Get ahold of Truman.

1839
02:01:04,385 --> 02:01:06,717
Prepare the world for bad news.

1840
02:01:06,787 --> 02:01:11,884
[Air Raid Sirens Wailing]

1841
02:01:13,661 --> 02:01:16,459
[Male Newscaster #1] We're getting
sketchy information that the mission...

1842
02:01:16,530 --> 02:01:19,158
has suffered massive failure.

1843
02:01:19,233 --> 02:01:21,167
And what we're
trying to do right now...

1844
02:01:21,235 --> 02:01:23,328
is to confirm that and find out
exactly what that means.

1845
02:01:23,404 --> 02:01:26,373
Repeat: We're getting leaks
from several NASA officials,

1846
02:01:26,440 --> 02:01:28,908
some rushing home
to be with their families,

1847
02:01:28,976 --> 02:01:31,604
that the drilling
was unsuccessful.

1848
02:01:33,214 --> 02:01:36,581
¤ [Chanting]

1849
02:01:36,650 --> 02:01:40,814
[Female Newscaster Speaking French]

1850
02:01:40,888 --> 02:01:43,652
[Male Newscaster #2]
This could very well be our final hour.

1851
02:01:43,724 --> 02:01:47,490
[Male Newscaster #3
Speaking Foreign Language]

1852
02:01:47,561 --> 02:01:49,495
[Male Newscaster #4]
We're gonna go off the air now.

1853
02:01:49,563 --> 02:01:52,498
Good luck and God bless.

1854
02:01:56,070 --> 02:01:57,867
- [Man #1] We've got incoming.
- [Man #2] I got tracks.

1855
02:01:57,938 --> 02:02:00,065
NORAD's tracking four
small incoming over Europe.

1856
02:02:00,141 --> 02:02:02,075
I think one's about to hit near Paris.

1857
02:02:02,143 --> 02:02:06,170
[Asteroid Shrieking]

1858
02:02:09,250 --> 02:02:12,185
[Screaming]

1859
02:02:25,900 --> 02:02:29,836
- [All Shouting]
- Reports are coming in.

1860
02:02:29,904 --> 02:02:32,771
[Male Newscaster #1] Martial law
has been implemented in 42 countries.

1861
02:02:32,840 --> 02:02:35,104
[Male Newscaster #2]
Once the asteroid hits zero barrier,

1862
02:02:35,176 --> 02:02:39,545
it will take about three hours
and 57 minutes to impact Earth.

1863
02:02:39,613 --> 02:02:43,208
[Sirens Wailing]

1864
02:02:43,284 --> 02:02:45,218
I guess we do it the president's way.

1865
02:02:45,286 --> 02:02:47,516
I'll order an evac.
You can remote detonate.

1866
02:02:47,588 --> 02:02:50,785
- You still don't think this'll work, do you?
- What I think is irrelevant.

1867
02:02:50,858 --> 02:02:53,827
- [Kimsey] We need to do it now.
- Fine.

1868
02:02:53,894 --> 02:02:56,021
- Can they still take off?
- We hope so.

1869
02:02:56,096 --> 02:02:58,189
You are the one
that pulled them into this!

1870
02:02:58,265 --> 02:03:02,224
That is my family up there,
so I don't wanna hear, "We hope so"!

1871
02:03:07,308 --> 02:03:10,573
Guess what, guys?
It's time to embrace the horror.

1872
02:03:10,644 --> 02:03:14,136
Look. We got front-row tickets
to the end of the Earth.

1873
02:03:15,382 --> 02:03:17,316
[Radio Static Crackling]

1874
02:03:26,560 --> 02:03:29,495
[Rumbling]

1875
02:03:36,504 --> 02:03:40,964
- Yeah! - Way to
go, baby! - Harry!

1876
02:03:44,178 --> 02:03:47,409
[All Cheering]

1877
02:03:47,481 --> 02:03:50,348
Yo, Harry! What's up, baby?

1878
02:03:50,417 --> 02:03:53,386
Hey, get that bomb outta there!
We got a hole to make!

1879
02:03:53,454 --> 02:03:56,981
[Sharp]
Houston, you're not gonna believe this,

1880
02:03:57,057 --> 02:03:59,685
but the other Armadillo has arrived.

1881
02:03:59,760 --> 02:04:03,161
- [Cheering, Applauding]
- All right, people, listen up. Settle down and focus.

1882
02:04:03,230 --> 02:04:06,757
- Mechanical, get on-line. - P.P.O.,
gimme a setup. - Your boyfriend's back.

1883
02:04:08,202 --> 02:04:10,693
- [Bear] Yo, Harry!
- [Shouting]

1884
02:04:10,771 --> 02:04:13,934
Hey, Harry. You miss me?

1885
02:04:14,008 --> 02:04:17,603
A.J., I got just five words for ya.

1886
02:04:17,678 --> 02:04:21,011
- Damn glad to see ya, boy!
- That's six words.

1887
02:04:21,081 --> 02:04:24,141
- Chick, walk 'em down.
- [A.J.] So where's this hole you need dug?

1888
02:04:24,218 --> 02:04:27,016
[Watts]
Houston, drilling has recommenced.

1889
02:04:27,087 --> 02:04:30,614
Do you think they can drill
250 feet in an hour?

1890
02:04:30,691 --> 02:04:32,716
They better.

1891
02:04:32,793 --> 02:04:35,455
Bring that piece on in, Bear.

1892
02:04:35,529 --> 02:04:38,225
Tractor pull.

1893
02:04:38,299 --> 02:04:41,632
- I'm comin' down!
- We got 250 feet to go.

1894
02:04:41,702 --> 02:04:44,796
It's our last transmission,
last drill head.

1895
02:04:44,872 --> 02:04:48,899
Punch it through.
First gear. We got contact.

1896
02:04:48,976 --> 02:04:53,941
- Come on down, A.J.
- [Grunting] I got this, man. Let's go!

1897
02:04:54,014 --> 02:04:57,973
Lev, the right engine hub. Houston, I'm
getting no response from the preflight sequence.

1898
02:04:58,051 --> 02:05:01,646
[Muffled] Come on, now.
This is not... Hey... Hey, come here.

1899
02:05:01,722 --> 02:05:05,783
Can you get me outta here,
please, Lev? Thank you. [Grunting]

1900
02:05:05,859 --> 02:05:09,124
- Ow! Jesus! Hey!
- Wait. Uh, shh, shh.

1901
02:05:09,196 --> 02:05:11,664
- [Watts] Lev, the right engine...
- Okay.

1902
02:05:11,732 --> 02:05:14,724
Lemme outta here, will ya? Just tryin'
to have some fun before I die!

1903
02:05:14,801 --> 02:05:18,430
- How deep are we?
- Seven seventy.

1904
02:05:21,241 --> 02:05:23,675
[Grunting]

1905
02:05:23,744 --> 02:05:25,871
- Whoa, they got problems.
- The gauges are spiking.

1906
02:05:25,946 --> 02:05:28,039
Methane! Shut it down! Back it down!

1907
02:05:28,115 --> 02:05:32,176
I can't pull back now. The bit'll
get lodged. We don't have enough time!

1908
02:05:32,252 --> 02:05:36,052
Whoa, whoa, whoa! It's gonna blow!
It's how we lost Max!

1909
02:05:36,123 --> 02:05:39,957
I know what I'm talkin' about. We can punch
through this. We can knock this outta the park.

1910
02:05:40,027 --> 02:05:41,858
This is our last transmission, A.J.

1911
02:05:41,928 --> 02:05:44,089
Goddamn it, if you're ever
gonna trust me, ever,

1912
02:05:44,164 --> 02:05:46,997
once in your life, trust me now!

1913
02:05:47,067 --> 02:05:51,436
- Harry, it's gonna blow!
- Harry, I know what I'm doin'. You just gotta trust me.

1914
02:05:52,806 --> 02:05:54,740
Make the call.

1915
02:05:56,677 --> 02:05:59,111
All right. Hold on.
I'm pushin' through her.

1916
02:06:03,784 --> 02:06:05,718
[Grunting]

1917
02:06:05,786 --> 02:06:07,913
I'm pushin' through her!

1918
02:06:07,988 --> 02:06:11,583
- What's your depth?
- Seven seventy-five. Seven eighty.

1919
02:06:11,658 --> 02:06:14,422
Take it up, baby! Ram it home!

1920
02:06:14,494 --> 02:06:16,587
[Grunts] Drive on down, A.J.!

1921
02:06:16,663 --> 02:06:19,325
Seven eighty-five. Come on. Come on.

1922
02:06:19,399 --> 02:06:22,459
- Come on, A.J.! - Punch
it! - Ninety-one. Come on.

1923
02:06:22,536 --> 02:06:25,733
Seven ninety-two. Seven ninety-five!

1924
02:06:25,806 --> 02:06:28,434
Drive it down, A.J.!

1925
02:06:28,508 --> 02:06:31,033
Seven ninety-seven! Ninety-nine!

1926
02:06:31,111 --> 02:06:34,410
- Breakthrough!
- Eight hundred! Eight-oh-two, Harry!

1927
02:06:34,481 --> 02:06:36,449
- Yeah!
- We did it!

1928
02:06:36,516 --> 02:06:39,917
- [All Cheering]
- Yes! - We did it!

1929
02:06:39,986 --> 02:06:44,116
- Yeah! Kid, way to go!
- I knew it, baby!

1930
02:06:44,191 --> 02:06:48,127
- It's not over till we get the bomb down that hole.
- Watts, they've got 38 minutes.

1931
02:07:08,415 --> 02:07:10,349
[Sharp]
Harry, you've gotta give me that hole.

1932
02:07:10,417 --> 02:07:14,114
I'm gonna need two more minutes.
I got a bent pipe jammed in the hole.

1933
02:07:14,187 --> 02:07:16,883
We gotta cut it out before
we can send that bomb down. A.J.!

1934
02:07:16,957 --> 02:07:19,391
- She good to go?
- Yeah, I'm all set.

1935
02:07:19,459 --> 02:07:21,893
All right.

1936
02:07:21,962 --> 02:07:23,896
[Grunts]

1937
02:07:26,500 --> 02:07:29,060
- All right.
- [Harry] A.J., come on! Make it fast!

1938
02:07:29,136 --> 02:07:32,435
I'm goin' as fast as I can!
There's a lot of gas pressure!

1939
02:07:37,911 --> 02:07:39,845
You feel that?

1940
02:07:39,913 --> 02:07:42,746
Harry, you gotta give me that hole.
The bomb is almost ready.

1941
02:07:42,816 --> 02:07:45,307
- [Harry] Pull that pipe out!
- Harry, I'm almost through!

1942
02:07:45,385 --> 02:07:48,183
- Give me 15 more seconds!
- [Rumbling]

1943
02:07:52,225 --> 02:07:54,921
Well, this is somethin' new.

1944
02:07:54,995 --> 02:07:58,055
- [Crashing]
- I don't think this thing likes us.

1945
02:07:58,131 --> 02:08:01,965
- That's 'cause it knows we're here to kill it.
- Whoa!

1946
02:08:06,406 --> 02:08:09,000
Hey, what's goin' on up there?

1947
02:08:12,879 --> 02:08:16,872
- A.J.!
- What the hell was that?

1948
02:08:16,950 --> 02:08:20,044
- A.J.!
- Goddamn it, I'm finished!

1949
02:08:21,655 --> 02:08:24,317
- A.J., you all right?
- Oh, lot of gas pressure in here, man!

1950
02:08:24,391 --> 02:08:27,224
- Get me out!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa! Hydrogen pocket!

1951
02:08:27,294 --> 02:08:29,888
Aah!

1952
02:08:36,269 --> 02:08:38,237
Whoa!

1953
02:08:41,641 --> 02:08:44,007
- [Grunts]
- Aah!

1954
02:08:44,077 --> 02:08:47,774
Oh! Harry! Pull me in!

1955
02:08:49,149 --> 02:08:53,586
- [Grunting]
- Aah! A.J., hang on!

1956
02:08:53,653 --> 02:08:56,247
[Grunting]

1957
02:08:59,259 --> 02:09:01,955
Secure the bomb!

1958
02:09:02,028 --> 02:09:04,826
Sharp, heads up!

1959
02:09:04,898 --> 02:09:08,026
Gruber! Get outta there now!

1960
02:09:08,101 --> 02:09:10,399
- [Asteroids Shrieking]
- Oh, no.

1961
02:09:16,977 --> 02:09:20,378
[Whimpering]
Oh, God, no!

1962
02:09:20,447 --> 02:09:23,575
[All Screaming]

1963
02:09:25,752 --> 02:09:28,346
Look out!

1964
02:09:30,857 --> 02:09:34,384
Help! Oh, no!

1965
02:09:34,461 --> 02:09:38,591
[Screaming]

1966
02:09:38,665 --> 02:09:41,725
[Panting]

1967
02:09:41,801 --> 02:09:44,736
- Do you believe that just happened?
- [Gas Hissing]

1968
02:09:47,040 --> 02:09:49,736
- Sharp, you all right?
- I'm okay.

1969
02:09:49,809 --> 02:09:52,004
- Bear?
- Yeah. I'm here, Harry.

1970
02:09:52,078 --> 02:09:54,603
- A.J.?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

1971
02:09:54,681 --> 02:09:58,447
- [Gas Hissing]
- We lost Gruber.

1972
02:09:59,753 --> 02:10:02,051
Gruber's dead.

1973
02:10:02,122 --> 02:10:04,590
Let's get that bomb ready
and go home.

1974
02:10:12,566 --> 02:10:14,966
- [Sharp] Oh, my God.
- [Beeping]

1975
02:10:15,035 --> 02:10:19,335
- Is there a problem, Colonel?
- The timer, the remote, the whole thing's dead.

1976
02:10:19,406 --> 02:10:21,499
What, the bomb is dead?

1977
02:10:21,575 --> 02:10:26,171
No, the trigger's dead. It must've
gotten damaged during the rock storm.

1978
02:10:27,247 --> 02:10:29,272
So how do we detonate it?

1979
02:10:39,426 --> 02:10:44,227
We have 18 minutes to zero barrier.
We got some bad news.

1980
02:10:44,297 --> 02:10:48,063
The remote detonator
on the bomb has been damaged.

1981
02:10:48,134 --> 02:10:51,035
That means that somebody's
gonna have to stay behind.

1982
02:10:53,607 --> 02:10:55,939
It takes two people
to fly this thing.

1983
02:10:56,009 --> 02:11:00,173
Either we all stay and die,
or you guys draw straws.

1984
02:11:00,246 --> 02:11:04,774
I say we all stay and die.
But that's me.

1985
02:11:04,851 --> 02:11:09,379
I'll draw. Let's draw.

1986
02:11:09,456 --> 02:11:12,892
Nobody's gonna draw straws.

1987
02:11:12,959 --> 02:11:15,553
- I'll stay and take care of it.
- Well, I can't live with that sort of thing.

1988
02:11:15,629 --> 02:11:17,790
- Nobody asked you if you could live with it, all right?
- Bullshit!

1989
02:11:17,864 --> 02:11:20,492
No way I will let you
volunteer for this...

1990
02:11:20,567 --> 02:11:24,298
so I can go back to my home country
like the man who didn't volunteer.

1991
02:11:24,371 --> 02:11:26,305
No way!

1992
02:11:26,373 --> 02:11:31,072
Hey, man, let's draw, and let's see
who's gonna stay up here and dance.

1993
02:11:31,144 --> 02:11:33,578
Guys, I-I-I know you guys
think I'm crazy right now,

1994
02:11:33,647 --> 02:11:36,514
but I would really like
this responsibility.

1995
02:11:36,583 --> 02:11:39,051
All right. All right.

1996
02:11:39,119 --> 02:11:43,180
- I can do it.
- Let's just draw straws and get it over with. Come on.

1997
02:11:43,256 --> 02:11:44,991
I ain't drawin' against you, Harry.

1998
02:11:45,124 --> 02:11:49,060
Well, I'm gonna draw against you, Chick,
so you better just go ahead and do it.

1999
02:11:49,128 --> 02:11:51,358
Just gimme this thing.

2000
02:11:58,137 --> 02:12:00,731
Is this good or bad?

2001
02:12:05,811 --> 02:12:08,644
Oh, man.

2002
02:12:08,714 --> 02:12:12,343
Well, we all gotta die, right?

2003
02:12:15,688 --> 02:12:18,020
I'm the guy who gets
to do it saving the world.

2004
02:12:18,090 --> 02:12:22,186
So, uh, let's go.
We-We got about ten minutes, right?

2005
02:12:24,030 --> 02:12:26,021
You plug this into the port.

2006
02:12:26,098 --> 02:12:31,331
Lift, press, hold. That's it.

2007
02:12:31,404 --> 02:12:34,862
Lift, press, hold. Shouldn't be
too tough. Even I can't screw this up.

2008
02:12:34,940 --> 02:12:37,602
I'll take him down.

2009
02:13:11,510 --> 02:13:14,240
Do me a favor, will ya?

2010
02:13:14,313 --> 02:13:17,476
Just tell Grace that, uh...

2011
02:13:17,550 --> 02:13:20,280
that I'll always be with her, okay?

2012
02:13:22,488 --> 02:13:24,422
Can you do that?

2013
02:13:25,991 --> 02:13:28,118
Yeah. Okay, kid.

2014
02:13:34,166 --> 02:13:36,259
Give this to Truman.

2015
02:13:36,335 --> 02:13:40,465
Make sure Truman gets that.
Get in there.

2016
02:13:45,444 --> 02:13:47,639
It's my turn now.

2017
02:13:47,713 --> 02:13:50,682
[Gasping] Harry! Harry!

2018
02:13:50,749 --> 02:13:55,982
You can't do this to me! It's my job!

2019
02:13:56,055 --> 02:14:01,152
You go take care of my little girl now.
That's your job.

2020
02:14:04,230 --> 02:14:06,357
Always thought of you as a son.

2021
02:14:06,432 --> 02:14:08,400
Always.

2022
02:14:08,467 --> 02:14:12,164
But I'd be damn proud
to have you marry Grace.

2023
02:14:12,238 --> 02:14:15,969
- Harry.
- You take care of yourself.

2024
02:14:16,041 --> 02:14:18,066
- Harry, no!
- I love you, pal.

2025
02:14:18,144 --> 02:14:21,079
Harry, I love you!
Don't, Harry! Wait a minute!

2026
02:14:21,147 --> 02:14:23,707
- My son.
- Don't do this, Harry!

2027
02:14:23,782 --> 02:14:26,376
Don't do this! Harry!

2028
02:14:34,727 --> 02:14:37,719
What happened?

2029
02:14:37,796 --> 02:14:39,696
That crazy, stubborn son of a...

2030
02:14:42,067 --> 02:14:44,865
[Grunting]

2031
02:14:46,005 --> 02:14:48,940
Well, this was a real good idea.

2032
02:14:49,008 --> 02:14:53,240
All right, let's go, Sharp.
Let's get our team outta here.

2033
02:14:58,150 --> 02:15:03,087
Come on! Let's get ready
to initiate thrusters! Let's go!

2034
02:15:03,155 --> 02:15:05,783
- Strap it in, guys!
- Get the O2 masks.

2035
02:15:05,858 --> 02:15:09,123
Are they green? Are they green?

2036
02:15:09,195 --> 02:15:12,722
I can't believe this is going down
like this. You all right?

2037
02:15:12,798 --> 02:15:15,790
- O2 vents locked, pressure loaded.
- Engine board is green.

2038
02:15:18,237 --> 02:15:21,035
[Woman]
T minus three minutes and counting.

2039
02:15:21,106 --> 02:15:23,734
Houston, do you copy?
This is Harry Stamper.

2040
02:15:23,809 --> 02:15:25,743
It's down there.

2041
02:15:28,747 --> 02:15:32,649
- Electrical systems primed.
- A.P.U. Is set. Oxidizers are loading.

2042
02:15:32,718 --> 02:15:37,417
[Man] Houston, we're outta here
in T minus three minutes.

2043
02:15:37,489 --> 02:15:40,617
Daddy! [Chuckling]

2044
02:15:40,693 --> 02:15:43,560
Hi, Gracie. Hi, honey.

2045
02:15:43,629 --> 02:15:47,087
Grace, I know I promised you
I was comin' home.

2046
02:15:48,667 --> 02:15:50,601
I don't under... understand.

2047
02:15:50,669 --> 02:15:53,797
[Sighs] Looks like I'm gonna
have to break that promise.

2048
02:15:57,576 --> 02:16:01,239
I, um... I lied to you, too,

2049
02:16:01,313 --> 02:16:04,510
when I told you that
I didn't want to be like you.

2050
02:16:06,452 --> 02:16:08,511
Because I am like you.

2051
02:16:08,587 --> 02:16:14,287
And everything good that I have
inside of me, I have from you.

2052
02:16:14,360 --> 02:16:17,022
I love you so much, Daddy.

2053
02:16:17,096 --> 02:16:19,087
I'm so proud of you.

2054
02:16:19,164 --> 02:16:24,464
I'm so scared.

2055
02:16:24,536 --> 02:16:29,599
I know it, baby, but there won't be
anything to be scared of soon.

2056
02:16:32,211 --> 02:16:37,649
Gracie, I want you to know
that A.J. Saved us. He did.

2057
02:16:39,051 --> 02:16:41,110
I want you to tell Chick...

2058
02:16:41,186 --> 02:16:45,054
that I couldn't have done it
without him, none of it.

2059
02:16:45,124 --> 02:16:49,356
I went to see your granddad just before
I come up here, Grace, and...

2060
02:16:49,428 --> 02:16:52,591
he told me that God
gives us children so that...

2061
02:16:52,665 --> 02:16:55,395
we could have roses
in December.

2062
02:16:57,803 --> 02:17:00,499
Well, you gave me a garden full.

2063
02:17:00,572 --> 02:17:02,540
A whole garden full, Gracie.
You really did.

2064
02:17:04,810 --> 02:17:07,608
I wish I could be there
to walk you down the aisle.

2065
02:17:09,548 --> 02:17:11,482
But I'll...

2066
02:17:13,385 --> 02:17:16,843
[Sighs] I'll look in on you
from time to time, okay, honey?

2067
02:17:19,291 --> 02:17:21,225
I love you, Grace.

2068
02:17:21,293 --> 02:17:23,022
[Crying] I love you too.

2069
02:17:23,095 --> 02:17:25,893
- I gotta go now, honey.
- Daddy, no.

2070
02:17:25,964 --> 02:17:30,697
No, no, Dad, no.

2071
02:17:30,769 --> 02:17:35,172
[Man On Radio, Voice Muffled]

2072
02:17:37,109 --> 02:17:39,839
[Watts] O.M.S. Pod pre-start.
O2 vents locked, pressure loaded.

2073
02:17:42,247 --> 02:17:44,374
What the hell's goin' on up there?
Why haven't you guys left yet?

2074
02:17:44,450 --> 02:17:47,248
We're going, Harry. Houston.

2075
02:17:47,319 --> 02:17:49,913
- We got O.M.S. Pod pre-start.
- Pod pre-start confirmed.

2076
02:17:49,988 --> 02:17:52,218
[Choking]

2077
02:17:52,291 --> 02:17:54,418
- What's the problem?
- I don't know.

2078
02:17:54,493 --> 02:17:55,960
- What's wrong?
- Fix it now!

2079
02:17:58,097 --> 02:18:00,190
No time, no time!

2080
02:18:00,265 --> 02:18:02,233
- What?
- What's that?

2081
02:18:06,038 --> 02:18:08,233
- Where you goin'?
- Come on. We're stayin', we're goin'.

2082
02:18:08,307 --> 02:18:10,241
We're stayin', we're goin'.
Make up your minds.

2083
02:18:10,309 --> 02:18:13,210
Sharp, get out of here now.
You got less than three minutes.

2084
02:18:17,649 --> 02:18:19,048
Come on, Watts.
Come on, come on.

2085
02:18:19,118 --> 02:18:20,949
Blow the bomb, Harry.
We're with you.

2086
02:18:21,019 --> 02:18:25,217
- Uh, it's stuck. Yes?
- You don't know the components!

2087
02:18:25,290 --> 02:18:30,250
Components, American components,
Russian components. All made in Taiwan!

2088
02:18:30,329 --> 02:18:32,754
We're gettin' tight
for ignition, Freedom.

2089
02:18:35,199 --> 02:18:37,429
Houston, we've got no fire.

2090
02:18:37,501 --> 02:18:39,401
- What does that mean?
- It means we got a busted ship.

2091
02:18:39,470 --> 02:18:41,961
A busted ship?
And I'm strapped in here.

2092
02:18:42,039 --> 02:18:44,166
I had a great spot picked out there.

2093
02:18:44,241 --> 02:18:47,768
Freedom, you fire that engine. If there's not
a way, you find a way. The clock's tickin'.

2094
02:18:47,845 --> 02:18:49,608
Let's go! Let's fire
that engine, Freedom!

2095
02:18:49,680 --> 02:18:52,911
You got less than a minute.
Don't think I won't blow this thing.

2096
02:18:54,685 --> 02:18:58,121
Sharp, get out of here.
It's gettin' bad down here.

2097
02:18:58,189 --> 02:19:00,316
I know how to fix it.
Please, move.

2098
02:19:00,391 --> 02:19:03,258
I- I have to take you away
if you don't move.

2099
02:19:03,327 --> 02:19:05,625
Watts, you gotta get that shuttle
started. You gotta fire it up now!

2100
02:19:05,696 --> 02:19:07,926
Damn it, Sharp.
Get off this rock!

2101
02:19:07,998 --> 02:19:11,490
I'm telling you, please, move!
This is how we fix problem...

2102
02:19:11,569 --> 02:19:14,766
in the Russian space station.

2103
02:19:14,839 --> 02:19:18,434
Because I don't want
to stay here anymore.

2104
02:19:18,509 --> 02:19:24,209
- [Whirring]
- Yeah! Finally! We can go home!

2105
02:19:24,281 --> 02:19:26,647
- She's coming back. She's coming back.
- We're hot!

2106
02:19:26,717 --> 02:19:27,979
Watts! Let's go, let's go!

2107
02:19:29,120 --> 02:19:32,886
Rain all you want, you son of a bitch.

2108
02:19:32,957 --> 02:19:36,120
Let's go! We don't have time!
Hurry, hurry. We got no time!

2109
02:19:36,193 --> 02:19:38,286
Initiate thrusters on my mark!

2110
02:19:38,362 --> 02:19:39,989
Two, one, mark!

2111
02:19:48,205 --> 02:19:49,866
Come on. Get some altitude.
Let's go, let's go.

2112
02:19:49,940 --> 02:19:53,171
[Yelling]

2113
02:19:53,244 --> 02:19:54,472
Freedom has max thrust!

2114
02:20:01,786 --> 02:20:03,720
Thank you, Harry.

2115
02:20:10,761 --> 02:20:14,720
[Screaming]

2116
02:20:14,799 --> 02:20:16,926
Shuttle's out of range.
Still no detonation.

2117
02:20:17,001 --> 02:20:19,993
[Grunting]

2118
02:20:21,505 --> 02:20:23,598
Something's not right.
Too much time has gone by.

2119
02:20:26,177 --> 02:20:28,543
Zero barrier's about
to be breached. One minute.

2120
02:20:28,612 --> 02:20:31,240
Harry, come on.
Press that button.

2121
02:20:31,315 --> 02:20:35,513
- We're goin' back and do it ourselves.
- Just don't. Wait one minute.

2122
02:20:35,586 --> 02:20:37,918
[Grunting]

2123
02:20:39,924 --> 02:20:42,791
- Dan, we're about to cross the threshold.
- Come on. Press the button.

2124
02:20:42,860 --> 02:20:47,763
Colonel, I'm askin' you.
Just one more minute!

2125
02:20:50,701 --> 02:20:53,898
[Grunting]

2126
02:20:53,971 --> 02:20:55,768
Press the button, Stamper.

2127
02:20:59,376 --> 02:21:00,934
Come on.

2128
02:21:03,480 --> 02:21:05,778
Harry'll do it. I know it.

2129
02:21:05,850 --> 02:21:08,580
He doesn't know how to fail.

2130
02:21:16,126 --> 02:21:17,889
We win, Gracie!

2131
02:21:19,530 --> 02:21:21,725
- Press it!
- [Beeping]

2132
02:21:51,228 --> 02:21:53,492
[Screaming]

2133
02:21:53,564 --> 02:21:57,000
[Man On P.A.] We have
detonation. Confirming detonation.

2134
02:22:13,684 --> 02:22:16,983
The two halves are gonna miss us
by 400 miles...

2135
02:22:17,054 --> 02:22:19,989
and most of the small particles
have been vaporized.

2136
02:22:30,768 --> 02:22:33,737
- Houston, we're comin' home.
- We copy that, Freedom.

2137
02:22:33,804 --> 02:22:37,570
Yo, Harry, you the man.

2138
02:23:30,327 --> 02:23:34,423
Kennedy, we see you.
And you never looked so good.

2139
02:23:34,498 --> 02:23:38,195
I never told anybody this before
but I hate flyin',

2140
02:23:38,268 --> 02:23:40,133
so it'd be an awful shame
to die now.

2141
02:23:40,204 --> 02:23:44,470
That's easy for you to say. I owe
100 grand to a bad-ass loan shark...

2142
02:23:44,541 --> 02:23:47,203
which I spent on a stripper
named Molly Mounds.

2143
02:23:47,277 --> 02:23:48,744
Boy, that's bad.

2144
02:23:48,812 --> 02:23:53,112
Kennedy, we are 100 percent.
Flap suspension control on full.

2145
02:24:05,696 --> 02:24:07,288
[Man]
Welcome home, astronauts.

2146
02:24:16,006 --> 02:24:18,236
Hey, guys, remember:
We're heroes now.

2147
02:24:18,308 --> 02:24:20,742
So that incident with me
and the gun on the asteroid,

2148
02:24:20,811 --> 02:24:23,279
let's keep that under wraps, all right?

2149
02:25:27,478 --> 02:25:30,743
Miss Stamper.

2150
02:25:30,814 --> 02:25:33,248
Colonel Willie Sharp,
United States Air Force, ma'am.

2151
02:25:33,317 --> 02:25:37,253
Requesting permission to shake
the hand of the daughter...

2152
02:25:37,321 --> 02:25:39,346
of the bravest man I've ever met.

2153
02:25:45,929 --> 02:25:47,897
Hello.
[Speaking French]

2154
02:25:47,965 --> 02:25:50,559
- Oh, my God!
- Hi, you're my hero.

2155
02:25:50,634 --> 02:25:54,331
Oh, baby, I wanna have babies with you.

2156
02:25:56,240 --> 02:25:58,174
Welcome back, cowboy.

2157
02:26:00,110 --> 02:26:04,342
Uh, Harry wanted you to have this.

2158
02:26:10,154 --> 02:26:11,849
He did, huh?

